Commentary: Some swing to begin with! This one moves away, the line is well outside off. Left alone.
Angled into the off pole, Latham solidly defends it.
Outside off, left alone.
This one jags back in sharply! Length and outside off, it zips through and also comes back in. Hits Latham high on the pads.
Just outside off again, left alone.
A maiden to begin with! A harmless nut to end. Outside off yet again, not played at. Not a lot of movement then in the first over for Anderson.
Yes and no but alll safe in the end! Shorter and on off, Young looks to drop and run on the off side. He takes off but is sent back in time.
Just outside off again, not played at.
Good length and on off, blocked.

FOUR! Off the mark in style! That should make Young feel a whole lot better. He has been short of runs lately but that is a good confident stroke. Shorter and around off, Young hangs back and pushes it through covers for a boundary.
Solid! Length and around off, Young gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Another harmless nut to end the over! Just the boundary from it then! The last ball is one outside off, not played at.
Starts this over with a length delivery outside off, Latham lets it through. Good pace in this surface but not a lot of movement so far.
Angled into the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Good solid start by Young so far! Length and on off, this is pushed to covers.

That is a beauty! Unplayable! Not a lot you can do with that but just hope it misses the outside edge! This is angled into the off and then Anderson gets it to leave the batter. Young is beaten as he tries to defend.
Now goes full, looks to target the pad of the batter, Young works it to square leg.
A dot to end! On off, Young hangs back and blocks.
Good length and on off, it is pushed to cover. Broad bowls this from around the wicket, like he usually does to left-handers.
Outside off, a big grunt as Broad delivers the ball. Easy leave though for Latham.
Tight run! Latham would have been in though! On off, this is pushed towards cover. Latham takes off. Stokes gets to the ball, turns and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.

Good half stop! Saves three for his side! Length and on off, Young looks to defend, this goes off the outside edge to the right of the fielder. He dives and gets a hand to it. It goes behind towards third man for one.
FOUR! Solid punch! Slightly shorter in length and on off, Latham hangs back and pushes this through covers. Trademark Latham there. The outfield is really quick here.

FOUR! That is the shot of the morning so far! That is creamed. Off the front foot this time. After a short one, Broad goes full and on middle, Latham shows the full face of the bat and milks it down to the long on fence. Beautiful. So pleasing to the eye. End of a very good over for the kiwis.
Good length and on off, defended.
Nice and late! Doing what he was not doing in the last game, that is let the ball come to him. On a length and around off, Young plays it right under his eyes on the off side.
Indecisive there! Another one just outside off, Young looks to play at it but then in the end, looks to leave it, it goes off the face and on the bounce to the slip fielder.

Another tight run but Young would have been in! On middle, this is worked to mid on. Broad runs in, picks it up with one hand and without gathering his balance has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
On the off pole, blocked.
A lot of movment into the batter but the line was well outside off. Left alone.
Makes the batter play, bowls it on the stumps, negotiated well by Young.
On off, defended well.
Angled into the off pole. Young keeps it out.

That has taken off! Really well played in the end by Young! This is on a length, it lands and gets big on the batter. Young does well to take one hand off the handle and defend it. He did that to keep the ball down. Really well played.
Outside off, Young leaves it alone.
Angled into the pads, Young lets the ball come to him and then works it to mid-wicket.
Tries to bowl the inswinger but the line is well outside off, left alone.
Closer to the off pole this time and defends it.
Angled into the pads, Latham works it to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, kept out.
BEATEN! Beauty! Length, angled into the off pole, lands and leaves the batter. Latham is beaten as he plays inside the line of the delivery.
That was a close leave! After getting the last ball to move away, gets this one back in from just outside off. Latham leaves it alone. It goes just past the off pole.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, defended.
On the stumps, kept out.
Three more! Just a mere push! Fuller and on off, this is hit down the ground, past mid off. He did not hit that way too hard and hence, it does not go to the fence. Three taken.
Solid defensive stroke to this ball on off to end the over.
A harmless nut to end. Outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.
Young gets off the mark! Angled into the pads, it is worked towards square leg for on.
On a length and on off, Latham pushes it to covers.
Well outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one. It was the tempter, Latham though evaded it.
On off, Latham gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
On the off pole, Latham defends it solidly.
On the off pole again, this is kept out.
Starts with a touch fuller outside off, Young leaves it alone.
On off, Young leans a bit and defends it to backward square leg for one.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Tom Latham throws his bat at it with some power. The ball races towards long off for a boundary. This is sgood batting from Tom Latham.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Tom Latham doesn't bother it.
On middle, blocked.
On a good length and outside off, Latham leaves it through and towards the keeper.
FOUR! That was a poor delivery from James Anderson. On a length and outside off, Will Young cuts it through point for a boundary.
On middle, defended back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again blocked towards James Anderson.
Outside off, Will Young eases it towards the slips.
Length and outside off, Will Young shoulders arms to it.
Touch fuller and on middle, this is defended solidly.
Matthew Potts bowls on a full length, Tom Latham blocks it towards mid on.
Outside off, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Back of a length delivery from Potts, this is defended.
Outside off and on a length this time, Latham doesn't bother at it.
FOUR! Length and on off, Tom Latham waits for the ball and punches it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! This is brilliant from the skipper. On off, this is much fuller, Latham drives it past covers for a boundary. Two in a row from the skipper.
On middle, blocked away.
Back of a length this time, Will Young defends it to short covers.
FOUR! This is pulled away stylishly from Will Young. Back of a length and on middle, Will Young pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off this time, Will Young defends it back towards Stuart Broad.
On middle again, this is blocked towards mid on.
On leg, Will Young looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards square leg. Single taken.
Flicks a length ball towards square leg for one.
Outside off and on a good length, Tom Latham shoulders arms to it.
On a length and on leg, Latham looks to block it but gets a thick inside edge and hits his pads.
Outside off, not played at.
Another one outside off, not played at.
FOUR! On off, Latham gives a firm push as the ball races towards extra covers. The fielder there gives a good chase at it but can only escort it to the fence.
Length and just outside off, Will Young leaves it alone. That was a good leave from Will Young.
Good-length delivery and wide outside off, Will Young leaves it alone.
This was much fuller and outside leg, Will Young looks to give a fine tickle at it but the ball hits his pads and races towards fine leg. Two leg byes taken.
On off, this is defended towards mid on.
Length and outside off, Will Young defends it to short covers. Oh, its a no ball.
FOUR! Full and outside off, Will Young cuts it through backward point for a boundary. 50 up for New Zealand.
On off, defended.
On leg and much fuller, Tom Latham blocks it to mid on.
Fuller in length and on leg, Tom Latham flicks it to square leg.
Blocks a length ball towards the mid on region.
Length ball and on leg, Tom Latham looks to block it but the ball hits his glove and bounces back towards the bowler.
On a length and down the leg side, Tom Latham looks to defend it but the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down.
Outside off and on a good length, not played at.
On middle, this is flicked towards backward square leg for one.
On a length and on off, this is defended towards the vacant short leg region.
Outside off, much fuller, Tom Latham drives it straight towards the fielder at covers. Single taken.
Much fuller and outside off, Will Young shoulders arms to it.
FOUR LEG BYES! Touch full and down the leg side, Will Young looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and races past the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Full again, Young works it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Two in a row for New Zealand and this partnership looks great so far.
Outside off, left alone.
On off and much fuller, Latham guides it straight towards the fielder at mid off.
Shorter and down the leg side, Tom Latham ducks under it.
Length ball on middle, Tom Latham defends it back towards Matthew Potts.
Bowls it outside off this time, Tom Latham lets it go.
Shorter and on leg, Latham ducks underneath it.
FOUR! Length and outside off, Will Young drives it past covers for a boundary. Oh, it's a no ball as well.
On middle, flicked towards square leg.
On middle, defended. Oh, another no ball from Ben Stokes.
Fuller and on middle, this is blocked back towards Stokes.
Fuller and outside off, this is drives straight towards the fielder at covers.
Full and on middle, this is flicked towards backward square leg for one.
On middle, blocked.
On middle, this is defended off the front foot.
Fuller and on middle. Defended solidly by Will Young.
On good length pitching on middle. Defended firmly.
FOUR! Gives it the charge. Full and on middle stump. Will Young gets down the pitch and tonks it over straight mid-wicket for a boundary!
Adjusts the length, outside off. Defended by Will Young.
Slighly fuller outside off stump. Worked to backward point.
Back of length outside off. Slashed to backward point for a single.
Outside off on good length. Played to gully.
FOUR! Through the gap! Slightly wide and full from Ben Stokes. Will Young strides forward and drives through the in field past covers for a boundary!
Straighter line on good length. Good defence from Will Young.
Outside off on good length. Nips back in and forces the batsman to play at it.
FOUR! Great balance again! Fuller delivery again outside off stump. Will Young drives well but a slight misfield from Jack Leach in covers allows the ball to run away to the fence for a boundary!

OUT! CAUGHT! Fuller and outside off, Will Young looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge and Zak Crawley at slips takes a beautiful catch leaning forward to his left. The skipper gets a breakthrough. New Zealand were looking great with the partnership and the Ben Stokes finally breaks it. Can England sneak another before Lunch. Young gives away the start. He was looking really good but now falls.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Ben Stokes

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Back-to-back wickets for England. Back of a length and on middle, Tom Latham looks to pull it but doesn't get enough power on it. A brilliant catch by Matthew Potts at mid-wicket diving to his right and taking it with both hands. New Zealand skipper walks away in disappointment.
Howout: c Matthew Potts b James Anderson

Commentary: Outside off, Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
On midde, defended.
FOUR! Thats a positive way to get off the mark! Short and wide from James Anderson. Henry Nicholls gets under it and slashes at it hard! Up and over gully for a welcome boundary!
Good length outside off stump. Jags back in off the pitch and Henry Nicholls blocks it off awkwardly.
On good length outside off stump. The around the wicket line is bringing the ball into the batter but Henry Nicholls judges it well and leaves it alone.
Fuller and outside off, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, not played at.
On leg and on a length, Devon Conway looks to block it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! On middle and much fuller, Devon Conway clips it away through the leg side for a boundary. This was effortless from Devon Conway.
Outside leg this time, Devon Conway looks to flick it but misses.
Back of a length coming into the batter. Henry Nicholls gets on his toes and plays it through point for a single,
Good Length delivery on off stump. Shoots up from the wicket and raps Devon Conway on his gloves. Fortunately the ball stays down.
FOUR! Delicately done! James Anderson strays in line and angles it down leg stump. Devon Conway flicks it off his leg slightly square of fine leg for a boundary!
Fuller length outside off stump. Left alone by Devon Conway.
Good length outside off stump. Defended solidly back to the bowler.
Full and outside off stump. Well judged and left alone by Devon Conway.
FOUR! Around the wicket line to the left hander. Slighly back of length and wide. Henry Nicholls dispatches it through point region for another boundary!
Full and on middle. Henry Nicholls works it to deep square leg for a single.
Slightly fuller and outside off stump. Left alone by Devon Conway.
Full and outside off again. Shapes away from the Devon Conway as he watches it go past him.
Full and slightly wider from Ben Stokes. Devon Conway strides into the shot and times it through cover for a brace.
Bowls on good length on middle stump. Devon Conway firmly knocks it straight to mid on.
Around the wicket line on good length. Nips back into the batsman and hits high on his pads.
Back of a length and down the leg side, Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at.
Length ball on off, defended at short covers.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Henry Nicholls drives it past covers. The ball gets behind the ropes for a boundary. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
Two to begin the session! Fuller and on off, this is driven through covers for two.
Broad goes full again, this is on middle, it is driven to mid on.
Drags his length back a little but the line is the same, on the stump, defended well.

FOUR! That is a poor delivery! It is full and wide outside off, Conway opens the face of the bat and drives it through cover-point for a boundary. Broad is going full but there is no movement at all. Easy for Conway so far.

FOUR! Consecutive boundaries! This is even better from Conway. Broad now has a chat with Anderson. Probably change of plans. This is a half volley, full and on off, it is creamed through coevrs. Another boundary. Runs continue to flow.
Drags his length back and bowls it outside off, change of plans maybe. Left alone.
Leg bye! Angled into the pads, Nicholls looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
On middle, this is worked with the angle through mid-wicket for one.

Three more! Really good save from Pope! Fuller and outside off, this is jammed out through point. Pope runs after it, he dives and pushes it back in. Crashes into the dashboard but no damage done. Saves a run for his side. The full ball isn't working for now.

Drags his length back but more runs for New Zealand! Length and on off, this one holds its line. Potts looks to defend, this goes off the outside edge past the gully fielder and down towards third man for three more.
Outside off, left alone.
A harmless ball outside off, left alone. Good two overs for the Kiwis to begin with.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
That is well fielded! Fuller and on middle, this is eased towards mid on. The fielder dives to his right and stops it well. Saves three at least.
On middle, this is worked to md-wicket.
On off, defended.
BEATEN! Nicholls was probably late on that one! Shorter and outside off, Nicholls was late in the cut shot. He is beaten.

DROPPED! Crawley is the culprit. It was not his catch but the first and the second slip fielder are so close, you can't blame him for going for it. Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Nicholls looks to defend, it goes off the outside edge between first and second slip. It is more towards Root at first slip. Crawley dives to his right and sticks one hand out but it does not stay in. A single in the end. Crawley tried to do what Bairstow did but it did not stay in. Will this prove costly now?
Full and on middle, this is defended off the front foot.
Touch fuller and on off, this is blocked towards mid off.
Length ball outside leg, Henry Nicholls looks to flick it but misses.
Flicks a full-length delivery towards square leg for one.
Goes fuller this time and outside off, Devon Conway lets it through and towards the keeper.
On middle, blocked away.
Full and outside off, this is left alone.
Goes full and just outside off, Henry Nicholls looks to defend it but misses. The ball just aired past his bat and towards the keeper.
Sticks to his length, on middle this time, Henry Nicholls blocks it out solidly.
Fuller and on middle, Henry Nicholls flicks it to mid-wicket for a brace. This is good running between the wickets.
Outside off, left alone.
Close again. Just outside off, Henry Nicholls looks to block it but misses as it goes towards the keeper.
FOUR! A shot to admire. Full and outside off, Devon Conway eases it past cover for an elegant boundary.
Full and outside off. Devon Conway shoulders arm to it.
On good length pitching on off stump, nips back into Devon Conway who gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Slighly fuller outside off stump. Fends it to covers.
FOUR! Gloved for a boundary! Short and angling into the body. Devon Conway swings at it and gets a glove through the fine leg region for a boundary!
Short again on middle stump. Devon Conway pulls it to the deep square fielder for a single.
Good length outside off stump. Punched to covers.
Slightly straighter and on good length. Played to mid on.
Beaten! Pitches slightly wider on good length. Devon Conway feels for the ball moving away from him and beats the outside edge marginally.
Good length angling into the pads, Devon Conway tries to work it to mid-wicket, gets a leading edge that lands just short of gully.
Fuller delivery on middle stump. Worked to mid on.
Full and on the stumps almost yorker length. Devon Conway digs it out back to the bowler. Maiden over from Stuart Broad.
This is full and outside off, Henry Nicholls guides it to short covers.
On middle, fuller again, Henry Nicholls flicks it to square leg for one.
Touch fuller and outside off, Devon Conway lets it through and towards the keeper.
FOUR! This was well-timed. Slightly shorter, Devon Conway pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Good shot selection from Devon Conway.
On middle, slightly shorter, Conway flicks it to square leg for one.
Shorter and down the middle, Henry Nicholls ducks underneath it.
Outside off, this is guided towards point.
Touch fuller on leg, Devon Conway tries to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards square leg. Leg bye taken.
Change of line this time, bowls it outside off, Henry Nicholls shoulders arms to it.
Outside off again, Henry Nicholls lets it go.
Much fuller on middle and leg, Henry Nicholls blocks it away.
Length and outside off, Henry Nicholls shoulders arms to it.
Back of length on the stumps. Devon Conway pulls it backward of square for a single.
FOUR! Streaky boundary! Back of length into the body. Henry Nicholls gets over it and places it perfectly between slips and gully for a boundary!

Short again into the body of Henry Nicholls. He tries to pull but manages it lob it up. Ben Stokes at leg gully tries to get to it but loses his footing and falls short of him. Henry Nicholls gets a lucky escape.
Better control this time. Back of length delivery on middle. Pulls it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Goes shorter this time and aims for the body. Henry Nicholls ducks under this one.
Full and on the pads. Works it to the fine leg boundary for a single.
Full outside off stump, Henry Nicholls drives it firmly to mid off.
Short and angled in. Henry Nicholls pulls it backward square leg for a single.
Full toss on middle. Slips out of Ben Stokes hands, under the waist. Devon Conway clamly works it to deep square leg for a single.
Full outside off, Left alone by Henry Nicholls.
Full on the stumps. Defended awkwardly by Henry Nicholls.
Full into the stumps. Henry Nicholls puts his bat down in time and digs it out to point.
Full and angling in. Huge appeal from England players around the batter. Clearly going down leg side.
Full and outside off stump. Devon Conway lets it go and has good carry to the keeper.

NOT OUT! Third Umpire took a while there! Full onto the pads. Devon Conway flicks it in the air towards mid-wicket. Matthew Potts Dives towards the ball and claims to have caught it. Devon Conway stays put and the umpires refer it to the third umpire. Soft signal was not out and there was nothing in to over turn the decision.
Wide of the stumps on good length. Devon Conway inside edges towards deep square leg for a single.
Full and outside off stump. Left alone by Henry Nicholls.
Full and wide again. Henry Nicholls not interested to play at it. End of an eventful over!
Slower one and outside off, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Slightly quicker angling it of off, Devon Conway guides it to short covers.
On middle and leg, this is flicked towards the mid-wicket region.
Outside off angling it away, Devon Conway looks to cut it but doesn't get enough bat on it. This races towards the fielder at square leg.
Full on middle and leg, Devon Conway flicks it past mid-wicket. The fielder chases it. Three runs taken.

OUT! CAUGHT! Much fuller on off angling it away, Henry Nicholls looks to defend it but misses and just gets an outside edge on its way. The ball goes straight into the gloves of the keeper. England have a breakthrough after 77 runs.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Fuller and on middle, this is flicked towards mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and outside off again, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms to it.
On middle and full, this is eased towards mid on.
Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it straight towards the cover fielder. A quick single taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off again, Daryl Mitchell leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Much fuller and on off, this is guided towards mid off.
Fuller and outside leg, Daryl Mitchell uses the pace of the ball and gives a fine tickle to it. The ball races towards fine leg and the fielder there does a good job. Couple of runs taken.
Shorter and down the middle, Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.

FOUR LEG BYES! Fuller and down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and races towards fine leg for a boundary. The fielder on fine leg gives it a chase but cannot reach it this time.
Slighly back of length outside of stump. Devon Conway raises his arms and watches it pass.
Good length on middle. Devon Conway knocks it to short mid-wicket.
Good length pitching outside off stump, shaping away from Devon Conway. Fends it awkwardly to point.
Back of a length, oustide off. Devon Conway easily lets it go.
Slighly fuller outside off stump. Devon Conway takes a slight hop and defends on the front foot back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! James Anderson delivers once again! Devon Conway tries to come forward a good length delivery on off stump. The delivery keeps its line and gets an inside edge of Devon Conway's bat and Ben Foakes takes a easy catch towards his right.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b James Anderson

Commentary: Full and at the stumps. Daryl Mitchell defends solidly!
Slighly fuller outside off. Drives strongly to mid off.
Back of length on off stump. Blocked by Daryl Mitchell.
Back of length angled into the body. Daryl Mitchell defends it back down the pitch.
Straighter and back of length. Daryl Mitchell gets on the backfoot and defends.
NO BALL! A good length outswinger on off stump. Daryl Mitchell plays at it and is stopped by the diving gully fielder. Ben Stokes over steps and has to bowl one more delivery.
DROPPED! The extra delivery almost works. Full and outside off stump. Ben Stokes manages to get a edge of the batter but Joe Root unlike himself drops a sitter. Massive let off for New Zealand!
Length ball on leg swinging it in, Tom Blundell looks to flick but misses as the ball hits his pads.
Outside off, Tom Blundell leaves it alone.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell gets on his knees and drives it past covers for a boundary. That was a well-timed cover drive from Tom Blundell.
Length ball outside off, Tom Blundell shoulders arms to it.
On off and full, Tom Blundell guides it straight to the fielder at covers.
On a length and outside off swinging it away, Tom Blundell shoulders arms to it.
On off, driven towards the fielder at covers.
Back of a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets it two minds but lets it through towards the keeper in the end.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, defended back towards Ben Stokes.
Fuller and down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell flicks it to square leg for one.
Back of a length and on middle, Tom Blundell blocks it towards the vacant short leg region for a quick single.
On a good length but really wide. Left alone by Tom Blundell.
On a length and outside off, Tom Blundell leaves it alone.
Slighly short and outside off. Easily left alone.
Fuller and slighly wide. Defended to gully.
Good length just outside off. Left alone by Tom Blundell .
Good length on off stump. Defended to short cover. Another maiden from James Anderson .
Good length outside off. Daryl Mitchell is happy to leave it alone.
Slighly fuller outside off. Nudged towards second slip.
Good length but wide and cant make Daryl Mitchell  play at it.
Good length bowling shaping away from the batter. Ben Stokes needs to make Daryl Mitchell  play more as this one is left alone as well.
Fuller this time but still outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell drives wide of mid off where James Anderson dives and restricts it to a single.
Inswinger this time from good length but wide enough to be left alone again.
On a good length and on the stumps, Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.
Much fuller this time and on the stumps, Daryl Mitchell guides it to the off side for a brace.
FOUR! On off and fuller, Daryl Mitchell lofts it up and over mid off. It takes a couple of bounces and past the boundary line.
Outside off, this is guided to point for a brace.

Full and on off, Daryl Mitchell looks to defend it but gets an outside edge. It takes an awkward bounce as it goes towards the slip and Jonny Bairstow just manages to get his hand on it. Single taken.
On middle, defended back towards James Anderson.
Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Length ball on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to defend it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards the slips.
Shorter and down the middle, Daryl Mitchell ducks underneath it.
Touch fuller and on leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to block it but hits his pads. A slight appeal but the umpire shows no interest. Oh, its a no ball.
Outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, left alone again.
Sticks to bowling it outside off, Daryl Mitchell lets this one go as well.
Fuller and outside off, this is punched towards covers for one.
FOUR! Tossed up on leg, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full and on off, this is guided towards point for one.
On middle, blocked.
Tossed up on off, Tom Blundell defends it towards mid off.
Fuller and outside off this time, Tom Blundell guides it to covers.
Fuller outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell fends it towards gully.
Back of length angled into the body. Daryl Mitchell gets on top of it and works it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length outside off stump. Shaping away from Tom Blundell as he lets it go with ease.
Ben Stokes gets straighter on a good length. Tom Blundell works it off his hips to deep square leg for a single.
Good length outside off. Defended confidently to short covers.
Straighter line on good length. Daryl Mitchell defends back towards the bowler and keeps the pose. That will be the Tea Break on Day 1.
Starts with a good delivery. On leg, Tom Blundell looks to defend it but the ball hits his pads. A slight appeal but the finger stays down.
Outside off, guided towards the cover fielder.
Tossed up on off, Tom Blundell eases it towards point for one.
Tossed up on middle with a hint of turn, this is defended.
Similar to the last delivery, this is blocked away.
On middle again, Daryl Mitchell defends it off his front foot and back towards Jack Leach.
Much fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell defends it to point.
Outside off and on a length, Tom Blundell lets it through and towards the keeper.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again left towards the keeper.
Much fuller outside off, Tom Blundell guides it to gully where the fielder makes a half stop. Single taken.
Length ball outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
On middle this time, Daryl Mitchell blocks it away.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended towards point for a quick single.
Bowls it on middle again, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the fielder at mid on.
FOUR! On middle with a hint of turn, Daryl Mitchell reverse sweeps it through backward point for a boundary. A well executed boundary by Daryl Mitchell.
On middle, defended.

EDGY FOUR! 100 for Daryl Mitchell! A fortunate boundary to get to the milestone but he deserves all the luck. He has been so good with the bat in this tour. Consecutive tons for him. Talk about grabbing an opportunity. He played the first Test because of an injury to Nicholls, scored a ton. He wasn't sure of playing this but was slotted in the XI due to Williamson missing out and now has another ton to his name. Probably has done enough to cement his spot. Gets there with a boundary down to third man. On a length and around off, Daryl Mitchell looks to defend, it goes off the outside edge. Daryl Mitchell is delighted and so are his teammates. Can he now continue to make it into a big one?

100 up for Tom Blundell. His third in 19 matches. What a brilliant knock this has been from the keeper-batter. He missed out on a century in the last game but has made sure that he gets to that milestone this time. On middle, this is eased towards the vacant short leg region for a quick single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell looks to loft it over mid off but doesn't get enough bat on it. The English skipper, Ben Stokes at mid off takes a easy catch and Blundell departs after getting to his century. An end to an excellent innings by Tom Blundell and he walks back to a standing ovation. England finally get a breakthrough.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Jack Leach

Commentary: On middle, blocked.
On off, this is defended towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle. Michael Bracewell works it wide of backward square leg for a single. First run in Test cricket for Michael Bracewell!
Lovely loopy delivery on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it off the front foot.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell leaves it alone comfortably.
Beaten this time! A fullish delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell looks to drive it away but gets beaten off the outside edge of his blade.
Angling into middle this time. Michael Bracewell blocks it out.
Stokes again angles this on off from 'round the wicket. Michael Bracewell tries to drive it but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
NO BALL! A fullish delivery, outisde off. Michael Bracewell drives it towards point. Stokes has overstepped and we have a No Ball here.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
FOUR! Lovely timing by Michael Bracewell! A fullish delivery that is drifting on the pads. Michael Bracewell clips it crisply through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, this is blocked back toward Jack Leach.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again back towards Jack Leach.
On middle, eased towards mid on.
Defends a fuller one towards mid on.
Fuller in length and down the middle, this is defended to covers.
Tossed up on middle, Daryl Mitchell eases it back towards Jack Leach.
On a length and outside off, Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
Outside off again, Michael Bracewell leaves this one as well.
Sticks to bowling it outside off, Michael Bracewell leaves this one again towards the keeper.
Much fuller and down the middle, Michael Bracewell defends it back towards the bowler.
Goes to bowling it outside off again, Michael Bracewell doesn't bother at it.
Another one wide outside off, this is left through and towards the keeper.
Tossed up wide outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
On middle,this is defended toeards mid off.
Drives a fuller one to covers for a quick single.
Tossed up delivery on off angling it into the batter, this is defended solidly.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again defended back towards the bowler.
Much fuller and on the middle with a hint of turn, Michael Bracewell looks to block it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards slips. That will be Lunch for Day 2.
Starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery on middle. Mitchell works it to square leg and takes an easy single.
FOUR! Daryl Mitchell is away with a boundary off his first ball in the session. It is a full delivery on middle. Michael Bracewell leans forward and creams it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Lands on a length, around off. Michael Bracewell blocks it off the front foot.
Stokes drifts it down the leg side. Michael Bracewell looks to flick it away but misses.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell lets it go watchfully.
FOUR! Another confident shot from Michael Bracewell! This is short and angling into the body. Michael Bracewell gets into his position early and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Third boundary in seven balls after Lunch for New Zealand! Short and wide outside off. Daryl Mitchell rocks back and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.
This is full on middle. Mitchell drives it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on middle. Mitchell blocks it out.
SIX! Ohh...signs of aggression from Daryl Mitchell! This is tossed up on middle. Daryl Mitchell steps down the track and launches it straight down the ground for a maximum.

Good stop by Jonny Bairstow, however, it is still three more runs for Mitchell. It is short and outside off again. Mitchell rocks back and cuts it through covers. Jonny Bairstow chases it and dives to keep it inside the playing field. Three runs taken.
FOUR! Another boundary and this is an expensive start from Jack Leach! 17 from the over! Tossed up on off. Michael Bracewell skips down the track and hits it hard down the ground for a boundary.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
This is full on off. Mitchell drives it to mid on this time.
On the shorter side, on off. Mitchell works it to deep square leg for a single.
A hint of away swing there! Stokes delivers it full and outside off. It is too wide though and Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
Another full and wide delivery, outside off. A harmless one and Michael Bracewell lets it go.
Pulls his length back and it is around off. Michael Bracewell defends it towards point.
A flatter and quicker delivery on middle. Mitchell blocks it out.
Slower in the air and drifting on the pads. Mitchell works it to short fine leg.
SIX! That is huge! Daryl Mitchell moves onto 149! This is a flighted delivery on middle. Daryl Mitchell dances down the track and slams it well over long on for a biggie.
A fuller delivery on off. Mitchell defends it off the front foot.

150 up for Daryl Mitchell! Brilliant innings by him and he has paced this innings quite perfectly here, stepping on the gas when needed. This is fuller on middle. Mitchell eases it down to long on for a single.
Slower in the air on middle. Michael Bracewell blocks it out.
On a length, on middle. Mitchell works it to mid-wicket for a single.
A length delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
Another harmless wide delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell is happy to let it go.
Stokes continues with his ploy of bowling outside off. It is a bit closer to the batter this time though but still wide enough for the batter to leave it alone.
A length delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell with another leave.
He keeps it on a length and outside off. Michael Bracewell does what he has done all this over, leaves it.
A fuller delivery on middle. Mitchell blocks it off the front foot.
Another straight delivery and full again. Daryl Mitchell defends it nicely.
Shorter in length but same middle stump line and Mitchell goes back to push it towards the leg side.
Fuller and outside off. Mitchell drives it to covers for a single.
Angling on middle and leg. Michael Bracewell works it off the bounce to short leg.
Nice use of the feet there! Tossed up on off. Michael Bracewell skips down the track and pushes it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Glorious shot! Overpitched delivery on off. Michael Bracewell leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Stokes pulls his length back and it is outside off. Michael Bracewell tries to punch it away but gets beaten.
Lands on a length, outside off. Michael Bracewell lets it go this time.
Angling into off, a length delivery again and Michael Bracewell is solid in defence.
Serves a length delivery, around off. Michael Bracewell blocks it off the front foot right under his eyes.

FOUR! Finds the edge but it races away for a boundary. Stokes goes fuller on off. It swings away a bit. Michael Bracewell goes for a drive but gets a thick outside edge. The ball beats the diving gully fielder and goes towards the fence.
On the shorter side, around off. Mitchell punches it to covers.
Again a shortish length by Leach, around off. Mitchell goes back and beats the cover fielder with his punch this time. A single taken.
A flatter delivery on off. Michael Bracewell blocks it out.
Shorter and around off. Michael Bracewell cuts it but the fielder at backward point stops it.
Tossed up on off. Michael Bracewell steps down the track and pushes it to long on for a single.
Slower in the air, on middle. Daryl Mitchell blocks it off the front foot.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
Stokes continues with this line, outside off. Michael Bracewell also continues to let it go.
This is the odd delivery that he will keep trying. He delivers a full ball on middle. Michael Bracewell drives it off the inside half of his blade to square leg for a single.
Bangs it short on middle and leg. Mitchell ducks under it.
FOUR! Supreme timing! Stokes delivers a half-volley, outside off. Mitchell leans forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Beaten! Stokes goes full and wider outside off. Mitchell goes chasing for it but the ball beats the outisde edge of his blade.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.

FOUR! Nicely played by Michael Bracewell again! This a fullish delivery but not a half-volley by any stretch of imagination. However, Michael Bracewell drives it on up and gets it through cover-point for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Michael Bracewell lets it go.

FOUR! Lucky there Michael Bracewell! Potts bowls on a length, around off. Michael Bracewell is cramped for room as he looks to push it away. He gets the inside edge and the ball goes past stumps towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
On the shorter side, on off. Michael Bracewell looks to pull but mistimes it.
A length delivery, outside off. Mitchell lets it go.
On a length, on off. Mitchell blocks it off the back foot.
A short ball but down the leg side. Mitchell looks to pull initially but then lets it go.
A fullish length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone comfortably.
Back of a length, around off. Mitchell defends it towards the off side off the back foot.
This is again, outside off. Daryl Mitchell lets it go.
Potts drifts on the pads. Michael Bracewell works it towards deep backward square leg for a couple.
On a length, on off. Michael Bracewell blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller length, on off. Michael Bracewell drives it straight back to the bowler. He fails to collect it cleanly and the ball goes towards mid off.
Shortish length, outside off. Michael Bracewell punches it to deep point for a single.
Serves a length delivery on off. Daryl Mitchell with a solid block off the front foot.

FOUR! Daryl Mitchell ends the over with a boundary! He is enjoying himself out there now! A length delivery on off. Daryl Mitchell stands tall and hits it over mid off for a boundary. Runs are flowing for New Zealand!
Stokes with a 'round the wicket angle and lands a length ball around off. Michael Bracewell defends it towards point for a single.
Ohh...close! A fullish length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell goes chasing for it initially but then pulls his bat back from the line of the ball just at the right time.
Bangs it short on middle. Mitchell pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Michael Bracewell with a comfortable leave.
Nicely driven but finds the fielder! Stokes goes fuller, outside off. Michael Bracewell drives it to the short cover fielder.
Overpitched on off. Michael Bracewell with another good looking drive to mid on.
A full delivery on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length, on off. Daryl Mitchell defends it from his crease.
Starts with a length ball around middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell defends it away.
Oh, that was close. Back of a length outside off, Daryl Mitchell looks to slap it but misses. The ball just aired past his bat and towards the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Change of length from Matthew Potts. Much fuller this time, Daryl Mitchell blocks it back towards Potts.
Tossed up, much fuller and outside off, defended towards short covers.
On off, this is eased towards the mid-wicket region.
Fuller and outside leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to give it a fine tickle but misses.
On middle this time, Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.
Action replay of the last delivery, this is again defended towards Root.
Touch fuller and down the middle, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards square leg and straight to the fielder.
Back of a length and wide outside off at 79 mph, Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
Fuller and wide outside off, Michael Bracewell looks to chase it but misses by a margin. That was close. Michael Bracewell gets a lucky escape.
Bowls it outside off, left alone by Michael Bracewell.
Drives a fuller ball towards the cover fielder. No run.
Just outside off and much fuller in length, Michael Bracewell defends it to gully.
A maiden from James Anderson. Sticks to his line bowling it outside off, Michael Bracewell doesn't bother at it.
Shorter one down the middle, Daryl Mitchell pulls it but straight towards the fielder at deep mid-wicket. Single taken.
FOUR! Length ball on middle, Michael Bracewell pulls it hard and towards deep square leg for a boundary. Jonny Bairstow gives it a try but could't get his hand on it.
Shorter one and on middle, Michael Bracewell ducks under it.
Back of a length this time, Michael Bracewell pulls it but straight towards the fielder at deep square leg. They rotate the strike.
Slightly shorter in length from Matthew Potts, this is defended towards mid-wicket.
Surprising fuller from Potts, Daryl Mitchell eases it to mid-wicket for one.
Outside off angling it away, Daryl Mitchell leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Another one outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Sticks to his line, this is also left alone by Daryl Mitchell.
Fuller in length this time, Daryl Mitchell drives it towards the fielder at mid off.
Daryl Mitchell punches a length ball towards cover-point for a brace.
On off, defended at mid off.
Much shorter in length, Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery on leg, Michael Bracewell flicks it to backward square leg for one.
A low full toss this time, Daryl Mitchell flicks it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Back of a length at 84 mph, this is defended towards short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter one from Matthew Potts, this is defended back.
Shorter and on middle at 80 mph, Michael Bracewell ducks underneath it.
Back of a length on leg, Daryl Mitchell doesn't bother at it.
Outside off and on a good length, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms to it.
Outside off again, Daryl Mitchell leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Keeps bowling it outside off, Daryl Mitchell doesn't bother at it.
Another dot. Another one outside off, left alone by Daryl Mitchell.
A maiden from James Anderson. Another one outside off angling it away, Daryl Mitchell just watches it go.
Length ball down the leg side, Michael Bracewell flicks it to the vacant short leg region.
On a good length and on leg, Michael Bracewell flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Excellent stop at mid-wicket by the fielder. Length delivery, Daryl Mitchell pulls it towards mid-wicket and the fielder does a diving stop there. No run.
Pulls a length ball towards backward square leg for one.
Oh, that is close! Fuller and on middle, Michael Bracewell flicks it towards square leg and just short of the fielder. He gets a lucky escape.
On middle, Michael Bracewell defends it towards the off side for one.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Michael Bracewell.
Another one outside off, Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
This one is just outside off, left alone by Michael Bracewell.
Stick to his line, Michael Bracewell doesn't bother at it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Keeps bowling it outside off, it was much fuller, and Michael Bracewell finally falls into his trap. He tries to defend it but gets a thick outside edge and Joe Root at first slip takes a good low catch. A crucial breakthrough for England and this has been a brilliant little spell from James Anderson!
Howout: c Joe Root b James Anderson

Commentary: Ohh...what a ball first up to face for Kyle Jamieson! Absolute cracker of a delivery this by James Anderson! He nails a inswinging yorker on middle. Kyle Jamieson does well to get his bat down in time and the ball goes off the inside half towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Jamieson blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! 500 comes up for New Zealand! Potts tries a bouncer on middle. Kyle Jamieson goes for the pull and gets a huge top edge. The ball goes in the air and one bounce into the fence.
Another short delivery that is angling into leg. Kyle Jamieson ducks under it.
FOUR! Good shot! On the shorter side, around off. Kyle Jamieson stands tall and punches it through covers for a boundary.

Potts comes 'rpund the wicket and serves a length ball around leg. Kyle Jamieson looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but the umpire says no. Pitching outside leg this, good decision by the umpire.
Potts bangs this short and down the leg side. Kyle Jamieson lets it go.
A fuller delivery, on off. Daryl Mitchell drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
FOUR! James Anderson drifts on the pads this time. Kyle Jamieson just tucks it fine and the ball races away for a boundary. Runs have started to come quickly again after that wicket.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Kyle Jamieson pushes for it away from his body but misses it.
An effort delivery on off. Kyle Jamieson ducks under it. It is too high as Ben Foakes jumps to catch it. He gets a glove on it and the ball falls behind it. A bye taken.
On a length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell lets it go.
This is pitched up on off. Daryl Mitchell drives it to mid on.
Broad starts the new spell with a shortish length, on the pads. Kyle Jamieson clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Broad bangs it short on off. Daryl Mitchell pulls it to fine leg for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Finally, Broad gets a wicket on his home ground! More importantly, it is another wicket for England and they would be looking to wrap this up quickly now. Broad has been going for his bouncers in this over and he bangs another one, it is around leg. Kyle Jamieson looks to hook it away. However, he gets a glove on it and Ben Foakes behind the stumps takes an easy catch moving to his left.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Stuart Broad

Commentary: FOUR! Tim Southee is off the mark straightaway with a boundary! Back of a length, around off. Southee rides the bounce and guides it through backward point for a boundary.
Back of a length and outside off, Tim Southee blocks it to the vacant silly point region.

OUT! CAUGHT! Back of a length and on leg, Tim Southee looks to block it awkwardly but fumbles and the ball hits the top part of his bat. It goes in the air and at gully where Root does no mistake. Two wickets in the over for Stuart Broad and England look much more confident now!
Howout: c Joe Root b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Short and outside off. Daryl Mitchell cuts it to deep point for a couple.
Tossed up on off. Daryl Mitchell works it to long on for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! England get their ninth wicket and they have done well in this final session to keep New Zealand's score under control. Leach bowls that off stump line but it is not that fuller in length to drive off the front foot. However, Henry goes for it and does it aerially. He ends up hitting it straight to Zak Crawley at covers. He takes the catch comfortably and looks like New Zealand batters no longer want to hang in there and are going for everything now.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Jack Leach

Commentary: Full and on the middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Tossed up on middle, Trent Boult dances down the track and lofts it over mid-wicket for a one-bounce boundary. This was surprising from Trent Boult.
On middle, this is defended to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell flicks it to square leg.
Shorter and on middle at 81 mph, Daryl Mitchell pulls it straight towards the fielder at deep square leg.
FOUR! Shorter one again, Daryl Mitchell pulls it hard and through deep square leg for a boundary. This was well-timed fro Daryl Mitchell.
Shorter and on leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to defend it but misses. Stuart Broad appeals but the finger stays down. Replay shows that the ball had hit his thigh.
Shorter and on middle, Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.
Goes fuller this time on middle, Daryl Mitchell blocks it away.
FOUR! Tossed up on off, Trent Boult uses his feet and lofts it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off this time with a hint of turn, Trent Boult gets down the track but misses it. He is fast enough to get back in his crease.

Trent Boult has done well to bring his foot back in time. Tossed up, outside off. Trent Boult gives the charge and looks to hit it away but misses. Foakes collects the ball quickly and whips the bails off. However, Boult brings his back leg inside the crease just in time as replays confirm it after the leg umpire takes it upstairs.
Tossed up on middle with a hint of turn, Trent Boult defends it to point.
On off, defended.
Wide outside off this time, left well alone by Trent Boult.
FOUR! This is brilliant from Daryl Mitchell. He moves to 181 now. Shorter and on middle, Daryl Mitchell plays a pull shot through square leg for a boundary.
Low full toss on middle, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Shorter and on middle, Daryl Mitchell pulls it again, this time towards the fielder at deep square leg.
Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it through covers. Jack Leach gives it a long chase and gets it. They take a comfortable two.
Brilliant fielding at deep square leg by Jonny Bairstow. Shorter and on middle, Daryl Mitchell pulls it hard towards deep square leg and Jonny Bairstow collects it diving to his right. No runs.
FOUR! Stuart Broad was trying for a yorker but ends up bowling a low full toss, Daryl Mitchell hits it hard and straight down the ground for a boundary. He moves to 187.
Leach delivers this slower in the air and slightly shorter. Trent Boult goes back and mistimes his cut shot.
Tossed up, outside off. Trent Boult looks to go down the track but then decides to avoid the shot and puts his bat inside the crease.
A flatter one on off. Boult blocks it out.
This is outside off. Boult resist himself again and lets it go.
FOUR! This time he smashes it! A tossed up delivery on off. Boult charges down the track and slams it straight down the ground for a boundary.

FOUR! Another boundary and New Zealand now reach 550! Another tossed up delivery on off. Almost a carbon copy of the last ball as Boult skips down the track and hammers it straight down the ground again. Boult is very happy with his shot and rightly so, these are crucial runs for New Zealand!
Angling into pads. Mitchell works it to fine leg but denies a single.
Broad with a yorker, around off. Daryl Mitchell digs it out.
A length delivery on off. Mitchell slogs it aerially towards long off. It falls in the vacant region and a single is taken.
A short delivery around off. Boult lets it go.
Back of a length angling into the body. Boult blocks it awkwardly towards the off side.
Broad continues his short-pitch stuff and angles this around leg. Boult ducks under it.
A fullish delivery, around off. Mitchell swings across the line but misses.
Good running! A full delivery on off. Mitchell just pushes it towards the long on and comes back for the second run.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Daryl Mitchell departs finally and with that the New Zealand's innings also comes to an end. A slower and wide delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell reaches to cut it but gets a slight outside edge. The ball goes back to the keeper and Ben Foakes makes no mistake taking a good low catch. England players come up to congratulate Daryl Mitchell and everyone gives him a standing ovation. New Zealand are bowled out for 553!
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Matthew Potts

Commentary: Starts with a very full ball outside off, It is shaping in Alex Lees just gets his bat down in time to block it..
Fuller and on off, Alex Lees drives it towards long off for a brace.
Much fuller with a bit of swing, Alex Lees defends it to the vacant short leg region.
On middle, keeps it full, Alex Lees blocks it away.
Keeps it fuller and on middle, this is eased towards mid off.
On middle again, much quicker too, Alex Lees guides it towards the mid off region.
Outside off, left alone by Zak Crawley.
Back of a length and outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
This is just outside off and on a good length, Zak Crawley leaves this one as well.
FOUR! On a length and on off, Zak Crawley drives it past covers for a boundary. This was perfectly timed from Zak Crawley.
Outside off, left alone by Zak Crawley.

OUT! CAUGHT! An early strike for New Zealand. Boult with a lovely delivery that lands on a good length and around off. It bounce sharply too and kisses the shoulder of Zak Crawley's blade as he looks to defend. The ball goes back to Tom Blundell behind the stumps and he takes an easy catch. Another failure for Zak Crawley but must say this was a ripper of a delivery by Boult!
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Trent Boult

Commentary: Southee goes very full and outside off. Lees blocks it out.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Lees lets it go.
Goes a bit full and on off. Lees defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Nicely timed! A fuller delivery on off. Lees just pushes it with full face of his blade, times it nicely and the ball races past mid off for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Lees with a solid block.
Ohh...almost drags it back onto the stumps! A full delivery, outside off. Lees goes chasing for it but gets the inside edge of his blade. It goes past stumps towards fine leg for a single.
Much shorter and outside leg, Alex Lees lets it go.
On a good length down the middle, Alex Lees defends it to mid on.
This is touch fuller and on middle, Alex Lees flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone by Ollie Pope.
Length ball on middle, Ollie Pope defends it back towards Boult.
On off this time by Trent Boult, Pope guides it to the fielder at mid on.
Length ball and outside off, Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Back of a length delivery, Alex Lees flicks it to backward square leg and rotate the strike.
Fuller and outside off angling it away, Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Much fuller and on middle, Ollie Pope miscues his flick towards point and straight towards the fielder.
FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Ollie Pope flicks it through square leg for a boundary. This is beautiful from Ollie Pope.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and outside leg, Alex Lees looks to give it a fine tickle but misses.
Fuller and on middle, Alex Lees tucks it towards deep square leg for a couple.
Fuller and on leg, Alex Lees flicks it to fine leg for one.
Back of a length and outside off, Ollie Pope looks to cut it but misses.
On middle, defended.
On a length and outside off, left alone by Ollie Pope.

Dropped! Length ball outside off, Alex Lees pushes at it away from his body and gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards Daryl Mitchell at first slip and he puts down a sitter. A lucky break for Alex Lees.
Outside off, left alone.
Bowls it outside off again, Alex Lees shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! On a length and on off, Alex Lees looks to defend it but gets an outside edge as the ball races through the third man for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Alex Lees shoulders arms and lets it go.
On off, this is flicked towards the mid-wicket region.
Back of a length on middle, defended towards short mid-wicket.
Bowls it outside off this time, Ollie Pope eases it towards the vacant silly point region.
On a good length, Ollie Pope defends it to gully.
Slightly shorter from Trent Boult, this is left alone by Ollie Pope.
Good length delivery, Ollie Pope plays a cut shot towards point for a brace.
On middle, flicked towards square leg for a quick single.
Bowls it on a good length and outside off, well left by Ollie Pope.
Back of a length delivery, Ollie Pope guides it to gully.
On middle, defended.
Much slower and wide outside off, Ollie Pope doesn't bother at it.
Length delivery on off, Ollie Pope drives straight to the fielder at mid off.
Outside off and on a length at 79 mph, left alone by Ollie Pope.
On middle, blocked out.
On a good length, this is defended back towards the bowler.
On off, Alex Lees pushes it to covers for a quick single.
On a length and outside off, Ollie Pope defends it straight to the fielder at point.
Length ball angling it away, Ollie Pope cuts it through backward point and takes a comfortable two.
On off this time, Ollie Pope guides it to covers. Good fielding by the fielder. There was a bit of miscommunication between the batters but they take an easy single.
On off, eased towards covers for one.
Fuller and outside off, Alex Lees slaps it towards the fielder at point.
Shorter in length and on middle, Alex Lees looks to pull it but misses.
On off, defended out.
Shorter and on middle, Alex Lees ducks underneath it.
Length ball and on middle, this is guided towards short covers.
On a good length and on off, Ollie Pope defends it away.
Oh, this was close. Much fuller and outside off, Ollie Pope looks to drive it away but gets an outside edge but luckily for him the ball falls short short of Tim Southee at third slip.
On middle, blocked out.
On middle and much fuller, Ollie Pope works it to mid-wicket.
On middle this time, defended out.
Shorter in length and on middle, Ollie Pope ducks under it.
Comes 'round the wicket and lands on a length on off. Lees blocks it out.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Lees leaves it alone.
On the shorter side, around off. Lees nicely punches it through covers and comes back for the second run.
On a length and a tight line this time, on off. Lees with a solid block.
Another nice shot by Lees! A fullish delivery on off. Lees drives it through covers and gets in the gap. He gets another couple of runs here.
Kyle Jamieson continues with a fullish length, around off. Lees drives it crisply towards the cover fielder.
Nicely bowled! A fullish length and there is a hint of away shape. It is around off and Pope defends it off the outside half of his blade towards backward point.

FOUR! Nice and fine! Lovely shot! On the pads, this is clipped fine on the leg side for a boundary. Runs flowing now.
On off, defended.
Tossed up delivery outside off, blocked away.
Bowls it on middle, Ollie Pope defends it back towards the bowler.
On middle, this is defended to mid on.
Fuller and down the middle, Ollie Pope flicks it to square leg for one. This brings 300 up for England.
Tossed up on middle, this is flicked towards short fine leg and straight towards the fielder.
Outside off, guided towards point for an easy single.
Back of a length delivery, Joe Root pulls it but finds a fielder at deep square leg. Single taken.
Shorter and down the middle, Ollie Pope ducks underneath it.
FOUR! Shorter and down the leg side, Ollie Pope moves to his leg and awkwardly slaps it through backward point. The ball goes behind the ropes for a boundary.
Shorter again, this is pulled but straight to the fielder at mid-wicket.
On middle and shorter, Ollie Pope plays a pull shot towards fine leg for one.
On middle, Joe Root pulls it again towards backward square leg. The fielder at the boundary line does a good job diving to his left. A couple of runs taken.
On off, Ollie Pope reverse sweeps it to slips. Daryl Mitchell throws the ball in the air to mock the crowd and ends up giving a single.
On middle, blocked.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
On off, this is flicked towards square leg for one.
FOUR! Floated up outside off, Root reverse sweeps to the third man boundary.
On middle, defended towards mid on.
On middle, defended out.
On middle this time, Ollie Pope defends it solidly.
Outside off swinging it away, Ollie Pope shoulders arms at it.
Drives a fuller ball towards covers for an easy single.
Outside off following the batter, Root defends it away.
Outside off at 79 MPH, Joe Root leaves it alone.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended off the front foot.
On off this time, Ollie Pope guides it to short covers.
Flicks a fuller ball towards square leg for one.
On middle, Joe Root flicks it to short mid-wicket for a quick single.
Flatter and on middle, this is defended at point.
Much fuller this time, Ollie Pope defends it back towards Michael Bracewell.
Length ball outside off, Joe Root cuts it but finds the fielder at gully.
On a good length and outside off, Joe Root drives it to covers and rotates the strike.
On a length and on off, Ollie Pope defends it towards the fielder at point.
On off, this is drives towards covers. A diving stop by the fielder at short covers. Single taken.

FOUR! There is is, another outstanding ton for Root and it has come just in 116 balls. Absolutely brilliant by the former English skipper. He seems a different player since the time the burden of captaincy has been removed off his head. A lucky way to get there but when you have played so well, you deserve luck. This is short and outside off, not a lot of room on offer. Root looks to cut but it goes off the underedge down to the fine leg fence.
Outside off, slower too, Joe Root cuts it to backward point for an easy single.
Bowls it outside off swinging it away, Joe Root leaves it alone.
Outside off again, left alone by Joe Root.
Keeps bowling it outside off shaping it away, Joe Root shoulders arms at it.
Another one outside off, Joe Root doesn't bother at it.
On a length and outside off, Joe Root looks to play at it but misses.
Length ball on off, Joe Root guides it to deep point for one.
On a good length and outside off, Joe Root looks to defend it but misses.
FOUR! Fuller and down the middle, Joe Root works it through mid-wicket for a boundary. This was excellent timing from Joe Root.
On a length shaping it away, Joe Root looks to defend it but misses.
Outside off again, Root looks to drive it but misses.
Length ball angling it away, Joe Root shoulders arms at it.
Outside off angling it away from the batter, Joe Root leaves it alone. That will be Tea break for Day 3.
Southee starts with a lovely outswinger! Pitches this on a good length and around off and shapes away. However, Pope is careful enough to just let it go.
On a length, around off. Pope punches it through covers and comes back for two runs.
Lands on a good length again and around off. It shapes away nicely from the batter and Pope leaves it alone.

An appeal from Southee! However, it is probably going over the stumps and the umpire says no. This is a good setup from Southee. He bowled three outswingers and has now brought this back in sharply. It is pitches on middle and hits Pope high on the pads as he looks to work it away. However, just a dot ball in the end.
A length delivery, outside off. Pope leaves it alone.
Angling on the pads. Pope just works it away towards mid-wicket for a single. He dives to make his ground, though the throw was well wide of the stumps at the bowler's end.

OUT! CAUGHT! So a wicket off just the seventh ball after Tea!  A brilliant innings from Pope comes to an end, a very special knock indeed. He was given the opportunity be the new management to bat a number 3 and he has justified his position here with a classy innings. He is disappointed with that shot but walks out with a standing ovation. This is a short delivery by Boult on middle. Pope goes for the hook shot. However, he gets a huge top edge towards fine leg and Henry at the deep runs forward a bit and takes a fine catch. New Zealand finally have a breakthrough and they would be looking to make the most of this new ball now. Jonny Bairstow is the next man in.
Howout: c Matt Henry b Trent Boult

Commentary: Another short ball on off. Jonny Bairstow ducks under it.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Jonny Bairstow lets it go.
Lands on a length, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it solidly off the front foot.
On a length and around off. Jonny Bairstow defends it off the outside half of his blade towards point.

There is an appeal for a caught behind but nothing serious as the umpire is not interested and even Boult signals to his teammates that the noise was probably because of the bat hitting the pad. A good-length delivery, around off. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball goes across him with the angle and beats the outside edge of his blade.
On a length, on middle. Root works it towards the leg side for a quick single.
Southee with a short ball and around leg. Jonny Bairstow ducks under it.
On a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Lovely shot and Jonny Bairstow gets off the mark with a boundary! Southee delivers this length ball on the pads. Jonny Bairstow waits for it and glances it past square leg for a boundary.
Lands on a length, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over and this is nicely timed again by Jonny Bairstow. It is short and wide, outside off. Jonny Bairstow picks the length quickly and cuts it past point for a boundary.
Bowls it outside off and on a good length, Joe Root guides it to point and straight towards the fielder.
On off, this one is much fuller, Joe Root drives it to covers for an easy single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, that's a beauty from Trent Boult. On middle and back of a length angling it in, Jonny Bairstow looks to defend it but has probably missed it completely. However, the New Zealand players think otherwise and there is a loud appeal for a caught behind but the finger stays down. New Zealand go for a review and UltraEdge shows that the ball had hit his glove. Jonny Bairstow has to walk back and New Zealand get two wickets in quick succession..
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Trent Boult

Commentary: Much fuller and on off, Ben Stokes defends it solidly.
Outside off this time, Ben Stokes guides it to gully.
FOUR! This is good timing from Ben Stokes. Fuller and down the leg side, Ben Stokes uses the pace of the ball and gives a tint flick as the ball races towards deep square leg and through the fence.
Bowls it outside off, Joe Root shoulders arms at it and lets it through towards the keeper.
Drives a fuller ball straight to the fielder at covers.
On a length and on leg, Joe Root looks to flick it but gets an inside edge and the ball hits his thigh. It rolls towards point. They rotate the strike.
Outside off, this is guided towards the fielder at point.
FOUR! On off this time and fuller in length, Ben Stokes dances down the track and lofts it over mid off for a two-bounce boundary.
On middle, blocked at vacant short leg region.
Pulls a shorter delivery towards square leg for an easy single.
Shorter in length and outside off, Ben Stokes shoulders arms at it.
On a good length on middle and leg, Ben Stokes flicks it to the vacant short leg region.
Yorker and wide outside off, Ben Stokes eases it to short covers.
Touch fuller in length and on iddle, Joe Root defends it solidly.
Outside off by Trent Boult, left alone by Joe Root.
Length ball on middle angling it in, Ben Stokes defends it to mid off.
2 runs.
On off, defended.
Back of a length angling it into the batter, this is defended towards mid off.
FOUR! This is perfectly timed. Length ball on middle, Ben Stokes flicks it past square leg for a boundary.
On middle this time, defended towards mid off.
On a good length and just outside off, well left by Joe Root.
This one was wide outside off, Joe Root doesn't bother at it.
On off and on a good length, Joe Root defends it at gully.
Fuller in length and on middle, Joe Root defends it back towards the bowler.
This is on middle and on a good length, Joe Root flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Sublime. Shorter in length and on leg, Ben Stokes pulls it hard and through fine leg for a boundary.
Drives a fuller ball straight towards the fielder at covers.
Back of a length and outside off, Joe Root leaves it through and toward the keeper.
Outside off this time, this is guided towards point for one.
Outside off again, left alone by Stokes.
On a length and on off, Ben Stokes uses his feet and slaps it but finds the fielder at deep covers. Single taken.
On off, Joe Root looks to drive it but mistimes his shot. The ball bounces back towards the bowler.
On middle this time, Ben Stokes flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a couple of runs.
This is outside off, Ben Stokes guides it towards the point fielder.
On a length and on leg, Ben Stokes looks to loft it but misses as the ball hits his thigh.
On off, blocked.
FOUR! On off this time, Ben Stokes leans forward and lofts it over mid on. The ball races behind the fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Back to back boundaries from Ben Stokes. This is on off, Ben Stokes makes room for himself and slaps it past covers for a boundary.
On off and fuller in length, Joe Root defends it to short covers.
FOUR! Outside off and on a length, Joe Root uses the pace of the ball and cuts it past the third man fence for a boundary.
On leg, this is flicked towards fine leg for one.
Back of a length and outside off, Ben Stokes slaps it but finds the fielder at deep point. Single taken.
Much fuller and on off, this is driven straight towards the fielder at covers.
Length and outside leg, Joe Root looks to flick it but misses.
SIX! Kyle Jamieson is greeted with maximum from Stokes! On a length, on off. Stokes dances down the track and slams it straight down the ground for a biggie.
Back of a length, on off. Stokes blocks it this time.
On the shorter side, around off. Stokes with a solid block again.
Back of a length, around off. Stokes works it to fine leg for a single.
This is full and angling into middle and leg. Root works it towards mid-wicket and the fielder there does well to move to his right and stops it with a dive. Single taken.
A short ball to end the over on middle. Stokes ducks under it.
FOUR! Aggression! Not from Stokes but Joe Root! Tossed up on middle. Root skips down the track and lofts it towards cow corner and the ball runs away after couple of bounce into the fence.
Fuller on off. Root drives it to long on for a single.
A fuller delivery on off. Stokes sweeps but he gets a top edge here. The ball falls luckily in the vacant deep mid-wicket region. Two runs taken.
SIX! This time he connects properly and gets a maximum! A fuller delivery on off. Stokes stays deep in his crease and tonks it straight down the ground for a biggie.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ben Stokes departs! His quickfire cameo comes to an end. However, this was always going to be a risky option sweeping against the off spin of Michael Bracewell. He got away with it couple of balls back but this time has to pay the price. This is tossed up on off. Stokes goes for a big slog-sweep but ends up getting a huge top edge. The ball goes in the air towards deep mid-wicket and Trent Boult running forward and to his right takes a good catch. The lead for New Zealand is still 148!
Howout: c Trent Boult b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Pitching on middle and turning into leg. Foakes tries to work it towards the leg side. He misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Back of a length, around off. Foakes looks to work it towards the leg side. However, he gets the leading edge towards covers.
FOUR! Edge but over the slip corridor! Short and wide, outside off. Foakes pushes at it away from his body but gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes over the third slip fielder for a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Foakes blocks it out.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Foakes leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Foakes lets it go.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Foakes gets beaten off the outside edge as he looks to defend.
A tossed up delivery on off. Root works it towards the leg side.
On the shorter side, on off. Root punches it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Lovely shot and great use of the wrists by Ben Foakes. Tossed up on middle. Foakes skips down the track and works it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
A flatter one, on off. Blocked by Ben Foakes!
Slower in the air, on off. Foakes defends it off the front foot.
A flatter one on off. Foakes with a solid block off the back foot.

NOT OUT! A huge appeal from Henry! The umpire though is not interested and Tom Latham takes a review! This ball is pitched on middle and is angling on the pads. Root looks to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards fine leg. A leg bye is also taken and the review taken by New Zealand also does not change the original decision as  the Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing the stumps.
A length delivery, outside off. Foakes leaves it alone.
Pitched up, on off. Foakes drives it to mid off.
On a length, on off. Foakes blocks it out.
This is full on off. Foakes drives it towards covers.

NOT OUT! Henry lands it on a good length, around off. Foakes decides to leave it. However, the ball hits his body and goes towards the keeper. There is an appeal for a caught behind and the umpire raises his finger. However, Ben Foakes reviews it and the replays confirm that the ball hits his body. So the decision will be overturned.
On a length and outside off, Joe Root looks to sweep it but misses.
Back of a length and on middle, Joe Root defends it solidly.
Much fuller this time, Joe Root clips it towards square leg for one.
Tossed up outside off, this is defended.
Pitches on off and turns into the batter. Foakes blocks it out.
A fuller delivery, around off. Foakes defends it towards the off side.
On a length, on middle. Root works it to fine leg for a single.
A fullish delivery on middle. Foakes pushes it to mid on.
A short delivery on off. Foakes pulls but gets a top edge towards fine leg. It falls away from the fielder and a single is taken.
Back of a length, around off. Root guides it towards deep backward point for a couple.
On the shorter side again, Root steers it towards backward point for just a single this time.
Henry goes full on middle. Foakes pushes it to mid on.

NOT OUT! Tossed up, around off. Root tries to sweep it but misses. There is an appeal but the umpire says no. New Zealand take a review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing stumps. So the original decision stays.
A flatter one on off. Root blocks it out.
Turning into middle. Root works it towards square leg for a single.
This is nicely tossed up, outside off. Foakes drives it towards covers.
Pulls his length back and around off. Foakes punches it to covers.
Tossed up on off. Foakes drives it back to the bowler.
On the shorter side, outside off. Root steers it towards deep backward point for a single.
On a length, on middle. Foakes defends it awkwardly towards the leg side. Bit of extra bounce there.
Lovely delivery! In that channel, around off. Entices the batter to drive and nips away just a bit to beat the outside edge of Foakes's blade.
Back of a length, outside off. Foakes defends it towards the off side.
Fuller delivery, around off. Foakes with a forward defence this time.

Ohh..dropped! Really, the catching in this game has been quite poor from both these teams. A short ball on off. Foakes pulls it uppishly towards deep square leg. Young in the deep there moves to his right and puts down a pretty straightforward catch in the end. A single taken.
Tossed up on off, guided towards short covers.
On middle and much fuller, Ben Foakes miscues his flick towards third man for one.
On off, this is guided to point for a quick single.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Ben Foakes flicks it to mid on.
Drives a fuller ball towards covers for one.
Flighted up on middle, this is flicked towards mid-wicket for one.
On a length and on off, Joe Root defends it to slips.
On middle and on a good length, Joe Root flicks it towards mid-wicket for an easy single.
On a length on middle and leg, Ben Foakes flicks it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Outside off this time, Joe Root cuts it to gully and straight towards the fielder.
Outside off again, Joe Root cuts it towards gully this time as well.
Length ball outside off, Joe Root looks to drive it but misses. The ball just aired past his blade and towards the keeper.
Much fuller on middle, this is flicked but straight towards the mid-wicket fielder.
On off, defended out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, this is blocked back towards the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, Ben Foakes goes on his back foot and blocks it away.
On middle, this is flicked towards short mid-wicket fielder.

FOUR LEG BYES! Outside off spinning it in, Ben Foakes looks to drive it but misses. The ball misses the stumps and the keeper as well. It races past long stop for a boundary. That was a good delivery from Michael Bracewell but didn't get the result he wanted.
On middle, Joe Root flicks it towards square leg for one.
FOUR! Back of a length delivery, Ben Foakes plays a controlled pull shot through mid-wicket for a boundary.
