On a length and on middle, Ben Foakes pulls this one as well but straight towards the fielder at square leg. Single taken.
On middle angling it in, Joe Root flicks it to mid on for a quick single.
Fuller on middle and leg, Ben Foakes flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Bowls it fuller and outside leg, Joe Root just gives a fine tickle as the ball races down the fine leg fence.
On off, defended to gully.
Tossed up on middle, Ben Foakes defends it back towards the bowler.
On leg, Ben Foakes flicks it straight towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Outside off and much fuller, this is defended towards point.
On middle, blocked out.
Fuller and down the middle, Ben Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! This is elegant from Joe Root. Bowls it outside off, Joe Root drives it past covers for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Joe Root looks to cut it but misses.
FOUR! 150 comes up for Joe Root. On leg and fuller in length, Joe Root flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary. He's been an absolute run machine for England.
Bowls it wide outside off, Joe Root leaves it alone. Wide called.
On middle, blocked away.
Length ball and outside off, Joe Root dabs it towards gully.
FOUR! Low full toss, Joe Root awkwardly flicks it past long on for a boundary.
On off, defended.
Flicks a fuller ball towards short fine leg for an easy single.
Tossed up on off, Joe Root defends it to slips.
Fuller in length, Joe Root flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On middle this time and much fuller, Joe Root punches it to covers for one.
On off, blocked away by Joe Root.
Back of a length and on middle, Ben Foakes looks to defend it but the ball hits his thigh and rolls back towards the bowler.
Outside off by Trent Boult, left alone by Ben Foakes.
Fuller and down the middle, this is defended back towards Trent Boult.
Shorter and on middle, Ben Foakes ducks under it.
On middle, blocked away.
Length and on off angling it away, Ben Foakes looks to defend it but misses and goes towards the keeper.
Lands on a length, on off. Root blocks it off the front foot.
Pitches it on a length, on off again. Root with a solid defence again.
On a good length and outside off. It seams away after pitching and Root lets it go.
On a length, on off. Root looks to defend it. However, the ball nips away just a bit and goes off the outside half of Root's blade towards third man for a single.
FOUR! Nicely timed! Half-volley on off. Foakes leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Ohh...what a ripper! Fullish length delivery, outside off. Foakes looks to drive it again but it is not a half-volley this time and the ball shapes away to beat the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, around off. Root defends it off the back foot towards gully.
On the shorter side, around off. Root leaves it alone.
A full delivery on middle. Root works it to square leg.
Boult goes for that big inswinger this time. Pitches it up and on middle. There is a hint of inward movement and Root flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Pulls his length back this time, angled across and outside off. Root lets it go.
Bit fuller but same line outside off. Root with another leave. A maiden from Trent Boult!
Bowls it outside off, Ben Foakes guides it straight towards the fielder at short covers.
On middle and leg and much fuller in length, Ben Foakes eases it to short mid-wicket fielder.
Back of a length and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks it solidly.
Fuller in length and on off, Ben Foakes defends it back towards the bowler.
Outside off by Matt Henry, well left by Ben Foakes.
Length and outside off, Ben Foakes leaves it alone.
FOUR! A wide full toss from Trent Boult, Joe Root drives it past covers for a boundary. That was a poor delivery.
Back of a length delivery, Joe Root pulls it straight towards the fielder at square leg. Single taken.
On middle, blocked back towards Trent Boult.
Touch fuller and on middle, this is again blocked back towards the bowler.
On a good length angling it into the batter, this is defended solidly.
Comes round the wicket. Length ball swinging it in, Ben Foakes looks to defend it but misses and the ball goes towards the keeper. THAT WILL BE STUMPS FOR DAY 3.
Southeee starts with a full delivery that is drifting on the pads. Root flicks it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Lovely shot to start the day for Ben Foakes! This is a fullish delivery with a hint of away swing. However, Foakes leans forward nicely and creams it through covers for a boundary.

FOUR! Nicely timed again! Good positive start for Ben Foakes! Southee delivers it on a full length, outside off. Foakes with a cover drive that beats the sliding fielder running to his left from mid off and races away towards the fence.
On a length, on off. Foakes blocks it out.
Lands on a length, around off. There is a hint of away movement again as Foakes defends it off the outside half of his blade.
Drifts on the pads and Ben Foakes is ready to flick it through mid-wicket. The ball does not travel all the way towards the fence but the batters run three before the fielder cuts it off.
Starts off with a good-length delivery, outside off. Foakes lets it go.
Goes a bit full this time, around off. Foakes drives it towards the short cover fielder.
FOUR! Poor delivery and punished by Foakes! Third boundary of the morning for Foakes! On the pads and fuller in length. Foakes flicks it past square leg for a boundary.
On the shorter side, around off. Foakes sways away from the line of the ball.
Boult with another short delivery on middle. Faokes ducks under it.
Lands on a good length this time, it is angled across the batter and Ben Foakes is happy to let it go.

SIX! What a shot! England are looking quite positive out there! This is full on middle. Root just reverse-scoops it over the third man fence for a biggie. Already the presence of new coach seems to be making an effect on the way, England are approaching their Test cricket.
On a length, on off. Root blocks it out.
Lands on a length, on middle. Root works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full delivery on off. Foakes drives it back to the bowler.
Lands on a good length and outside off. Foakes with a careful leave.
Another good-length delivery, outside off. It is a harmless one and Foakes lets it go.
Boult with a short delivery on off. Root lets it go.

FOUR! Lovely shot, this is Root at his best! England move to 500 now! On a length, around off. Root just waits for it and guides it through the gully region and beats the diving fielder near the third man fence for a boundary.
Beaten! Lands on a length, around off and it is again that angle that takes the ball across the batter. Root looks to guide it away again but misses.
On a length, around off. Root dabs it towards point for a single.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Foakes leaves it alone.
Comes 'round the wicket and angles a length ball on middle. Foakes works it to fine leg for a single.
Southee bangs it short, around off. Foakes pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and comes back for the second run. Both these batters have looked extremely comfortable in the middle.

FOUR! Another boundary and runs are flowing now! Southee with a short delivery from 'round the wicket angling into the body. Foakes gets into the position early and gets on the top of the bounce to pull it away towards deep backward square leg for a boundary. 100 partnership also comes up!
A short delivery on middle again. Foakes pulls it towards short backward square leg.
FOUR! Fifty for Ben Foakes! Another top-class innings from the wicketkeeper batter! On the shorter side, around off. Foakes rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a lovely boundary.
Southee with a short ball on the body. Foakes pulls it but finds the fielder at short backward square leg again.
FOUR! Ben Foakes with another boundary! Southee decides to go full this time, on off. Foakes drives and drives it well through mid off for a boundary.14 runs from the over!
On a length, angling into off from 'round the wicket. Root drives it without much timing towards mid off.
On the shorter side, around off. Root rides the bounce and blocks it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Trent Boult strikes and end of a brilliant knock by Joe Root! A much-needed wicket for New Zealand, England were moving at a rapid rate this morning. Boult delivers a full ball which is slower in pace on off. Root drives but is a tad early because of the lack of the pace of the ball. It goes bit uppishly towards Southee at short covers and he takes a fine low catch. Root is disappointed but he has played another magnificent innings and walks off to a standing ovation.
Howout: c Tim Southee b Trent Boult

Commentary: On a length, on off. Broad blocks it out.
A fullish delivery angling into middle. Broad defends it towards the leg side.
Boult serves a length delivery on off. Broad blocks it off the back foot.
A length ball, around off. Foakes stays back and punches it through covers for a single.
Soutee angles it into the pads. Broad flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Ouside off, left alone by Ben Foakes.
Good length, wide outside off. Ben Foakes leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, outside off. Foakes does not chase it at all.
Touch fuller, outside off. Foakes defends it to cover.
Length ball, on off. Broad stands tall and defends it out.
Touch full, outside off, shaping away a touch. Broad looks to chase it but thinks otherwise by the time the ball gets near him.
FOUR! Nicely played. Touch short, on the pads. Broad hangs back and flicks it to fine leg for a boundary.
Length and on off. Broad defends it out watchfully.
Full length, on off. Broad blocks it out solidly.
Good length, outside off. Broad looks to chase it but misses.
Tossed up, full and on off. Foakes works it to short leg for a single.
FOUR! TOP SHOT! It is full and outside off. Stuart Broad gets low and paddles it down to fine leg for a beautiful boundary. Brilliantly played.
Flighted and full, on leg. Broad tucks it to the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a brilliant catch by Daryl Mitchell. It is flighted and full, outside off. Stuart Broad hangs back and throws his blade at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of first slip. Daryl Mitchell makes a full stretched dive to his right and takes a stunning one-handed catch. England lose another wicket in the morning.
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: On off, defened out.
Much flatter, on the fourth stump. Potts defends it to covers. A great over by Michael Bracewell comes to an end.
Too full and too straight, on the pads. Ben Foakes tries to flick it away but is unable to connect cleanly.
Full length, on off. Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Full length, outside off. Foakes tries to go for the drive but gets beaten all ends up.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Ben Foakes lets it sail past him.
Angles it in this time, full and on off. Foakes flicks it to square leg.
Full length, wide outside off. Foakes reaches out and hits it back to the bowler off the toe end.
On off, defended out solidly.
Floated and full, around off. Potts blocks it out watchfully.

OUT! RUN OUT! A miscommunication and Matthew Potts has his head in his hands, as New Zealand see the back of Ben Foakes. It is fuller and on off. Potts stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket. Ben Foakes comes a long way down the track looking for a single but was sent back. Henry Nicholls throws it sharply to the bowler who clips the bails to send back a set-batter in Foakes.
Howout: run out (Henry Nicholls / Michael Bracewell)

Commentary: Full and on off. Pots eases it to long on for a single.
Around off, Leach uses his feet and blocks it out.
Touch quicker, on off. Leach gets on his front foot and blocks it out.
Full and outside off, Matthew Potts leans forward and plays at it, manages a thickish outside edge that goes through gully and point for a brace.

OUT! BOWLED! An inswinging yorker from Boult has proved to be too difficult for Matthew Potts to handle. This is on middle and swinging in right in the blockhole. Matthew Potts looks to work it away but ends up missing it completely and watches his leg stump being dismantled. Trent Boult has been outstanding in this test match and gets his 10th five-wicket haul in Test cricket. He has bowled his heart out on this pretty good batting deck and deserves this five-wicket haul.
Howout: b Trent Boult

Commentary: Back of a length, wide of off. James Anderson leaves it alone.
Some swing as well! It is full and outside off. This one leaves  the batter with ease. James Anderson tries to push it away but fails to do so.
A length ball, on the pads, James Anderson flicks it to fine leg for just a single. He gets off the mark. England still trail by 22.
Full length, just outside off. Leach gets squared up as he tries to defend it out.
Flatter deivery outside off stump. James Anderson slashes at it and misses.
Straight and on a good length. James Anderson defends it.
FOUR! James Anderson wants to go down swinging. Slightly full on middle, James Anderson goes on his knees and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Reverse sweep this time! Full outside off stump. James Anderson gets innovative and reverse sweeps the ball brilliantly towards the vacant third-man boundary for a four!
Floated full and outside off stump. James Anderson tries to play at it but misses.
Flatter and outside off stump. James Anderson knocks it towards the cover fielder.
Slightly full on middle stump. Jack Leach nudges it towards square leg.
Back of length angling into the body. Jack Leach gets on top of the delivery and awkwardly plays it towards gully.
Full on off stump. Jack Leach drives it to short mid on.
On a good length, shaping away outside off stump. Jack Leach knocks it towards gully.
Straighter line on a good length, beats the outside edge of Jack Leach.

Review Lost! Full yorker-length once again to the end the over. Jack Leach gets an inside edge onto his pads. New Zealand review but replays confirm the inside edge and New Zealand lose all their reviews.
Good length delivery that kept its line. James Anderson tries to slog and the ball misses the leg stump bails by a whisker.

OUT! STUMPED! Tom Blundell with quick hands behind the wickets and England's innings comes to an end. It is tossed up, around middle. James Anderson moves to the leg side as the ball turns down leg, although he is unable to get his shot away. He is out of the crease because of the charge and Tom Blundell makes no mistake behind the sticks.
Howout: st Tom Blundell b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: James Anderson starts with a good-length ball, from around the wicket. Latham defends it out solidly.
This is on a length, outside off. Latham hangs his blade out and blocks it to covers.
On a length, around off. Latham blocks it out solidly.
FOUR! Incredible shot to get off the mark. It is overpitched full and on off. Tom Latham leans in and drives it down the ground through mid on for a boundary.

OUT! TIMBER! James Anderson draws the first blood. Just the start England were looking for. This one lands on a length, touch outside off. Tom Latham misjudges the line of the delivery and shoulders his arms, as he thinks this would leave him. Although, this one jags back in to disturb the stumps. 650th Test wicket for James Anderson! What a champion he is!
Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary: This one slides down the leg side. Conway misses his flick. The keeper flies to his right and gathers the ball really well.
Stuart Broad asking the right question straight away. It is a length ball, in the channel. Will Young looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full length, outside off. Young defends it back to the bowler.
WOAH! It is a length ball, wide outside off. This one moves in a long way. Luckily for Young it goes past the off pole.
This one leaves the batter. Shorter, outside off. Young leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, wide outside off. Young leaves it alone for the keeper.
A maiden to start with for Broad! It is a length ball, on top of off. Young hangs back and defends it out solidly.
Full length, outside off, little bit of movement. Devon Conway defends it on the front foot and gets an inside edge to the leg side.
Good length, wide outside off. This one nips in off the deck. Devon Conway shoulders his arms and sees the ball go over his stumps.
Length and on off, defended out.

Really tight! An appeal for lbw but turned down. It is on a length, lands outside off and jabs back in, although with some extra bounce. Conway fails to defend it out and gets hit above his thigh pad. The umpire thinks it is too high.

Touch fuller and on off. Conway drives it down the ground. Alex Lees gives it a chase, puts in a dive near the ropes to pull the ball back in time, although the momentum takes him through his dive and he crashes his shin on the advertising board. That must've hurt. The batters though run four runs.
On a length, outside off, nips in off the deck. Conway gets struck on his pads. Another great over by Anderson comes to an end.
Full length, around off. Young blocks it out solidly.
Good length, outside off. Young lets it be.
Length ball, outside off, shapes away a touch. Young gets on his front foot but keeps the blade with himself.
An inswinger now. Fuller, around off. Young defends it out watchfully on the back foot.
This is odd one, which stays a bit low. Length and around off. Young stays back and tries to run it down the third man but only finds Jonny Bairstow at the slips.
FOUR! Will Young gets his first boundary of the game. It is overpitch, around off. Young gets in line and strokes it past Alex Lees at mid on for a fine boundary. The lead moves to 26 now.
Anderson angles on into the pads from 'round the wicket. Conway tucks it to the leg side.
Full length, on off. Conway defends it back to the bowler.
Three dots in a row! A short leg comes in place now. Anderson angles in, on a length, around off. Conway gets an inside-edge onto the pads.
Full length, on the pads. Conway flicks it to deep square leg and crosses for a single,
Fuller and at the stumps. Young fends it down to covers.
Length ball, on off, blocked out solidly.
Broad goes full and drifts down the leg side. Conway looks to flick it away but misses.
Ohh...lovely delivery! Lands on a good length and it jags back in and pitches around off. Conway looks to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten off the inside edge.
FOUR! Good shot! A fullish delivery on off. Conway drives it on the up and right of mid on fielder for a boundary.
Lands on a length, on off. Conway blocks it off the front foot.
A fullish delivery on off. Conway with a forward defence towards short cover.
Lands on a length, outside off. It seams away a bit and Conway lets it go.
Full length, into the pads. Young flicks it to the leg side but is unable to find the gap.
Length ball, on off. Young pushes it to cover for one.

Back of a length, around off. Conway tries to defend it out but gets it to fly off the top of the blade and over the slip cordon. Joe Root gives it a chase and pulls it back just in time to save a boundary. Two runs taken.
Good length, angled down leg. Conway shuffles inside the line but gets hit aroud his hips.
Short and on off, defended out watchfully.
Length, around middle and leg. Conway tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Conway.
Length ball, around off. Conway leans forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Full length, outside off. This one stays a touch low. Conway leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Conway has no stroke to offer.
Very full and on off. Conway blocks it out.
FOUR! Great shot! It is a full-length ball, around off. Conway opens the face and creams it past mid off for a boundary.
Good length, around off. Young defends it out watchfully.
Shorter this time, on off. Young uses the depth of the crease and blocks it to the leg side.
Length delivery, around the hips. Young tucks it to square leg and rotates the strike.
Matthew Potts comes around the wicket now. Goes full and on off. Conway blocks it back to the bowler.
Full length, outside off. Conway smothers it into covers for a single. It will be Young to face the final delivery before Lunch.
It is full and on the pads. This one squares Young a little bit but he manages to squeeze it out watchfully. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4.
Broad starts with a length delivery angling into off. Conway blocks it towards the leg side.
Pitches it on a length again, almost the same line, on off. Conway is solid in defence.
Goes a bit straighter this time, on middle and leg. Conway defends it off the bounce towards short leg.
A fullish delivery on off. Conway defends it off the inside half of his blade.
Broad goes full again, not an half-volley though and Conway is happy to defend it again.
A full delivery that drifts on the pads. Conway works it to fine leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Conway with a solid block.
Drifting down the leg side this time. Conway lets it go.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Bit of away swing there and Conway leaves it carefully.
Angling into middle and fuller. Conway works it towards mid-wicket.
Serves a length delivery on off. Conway blocks it out.
On a length, around off at 135 kph. Conway defends it from his crease.
On a good length and outside off. Young leaves it alone. Bit of inward movement after it passes the batter.

FOUR! Edge but it has beaten gully and races away for a boundary! A good length delivery, around off. Young defends it with soft hand and gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes off the shoulder of his blade left of diving gully fielder for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Young defends it with soft hand towards the off side again.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short and wide, outside off. Young cuts it but cuts it off the front foot more or less and the ball passes through point for a boundary.
Lands on a length, around off. Young defends it but gets a thick outside edge that falls short of the third slip fielder.
On a length, on middle. Young works it towards the leg side.
Potts drifts down the leg side. Conway looks to flick it but misses.
What a ripper! Lands on a good length, around off. Conway looks to defend but the ball seams away a bit and beats the outside edge of his blade.
On a length, on off. Conway blocks it out.
Full and outside offstump. Defended solidly by Devon Conway back to the bowler.
Wide outside off stump and slightly full. Left alone by Devon Conway.
Back of length angling into the body. Devon Conway tries to play it down leg side and misses. Ben Foakes makes a diving stop high to his right and prevents any byes.
On a good length and straight. Will Young works it fine of deep square leg for a brace.
Full delivery outside off stump. Will Young watches it go by to the keeper.
Good length delivery outside off stump. Will Young happy to let it go again.
Full and outside off. Will Young plays at it and mistimes it towards mid on.
On a length delivery outside off stump. Will Young lets it go again.
On a good length outside off. Will Young plays at it and gets a thick outside edge into the ground. Ben Stokes in gully dives to his right and stops it.

FOUR BYES! Potts with another delivery that drifts down the leg side. He gets a good shape into the batter this time but the line is not right. Once, Conway misses his flick it goes past way wide of diving Foakes to his right for a boundary.
Gets his line right this time! On a good length and around off. It jags back in sharply and beats the inside edge of Conway's blade.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Left alone by Conway.
It is wider outside off again. Conway with another safe leave.
Lands on a length, on middle. Conway blocks it out.
Full and on leg stump. Devon Conway looks to flick it towards square leg but manages to find Ollie Pope who is placed at short leg.
Floats it into the batter from outside off stump. Knocks it down to short leg.
On a good length just outside off stump. Worked it around towards backward square leg.
Pitches it outside off and gets a good turn into the batter. Conway with a solid block.
Goes fuller on off. Conway defends it off the front foot this time.
Continues with that line, around off and spins it in. Conway does well to defend it off the front foot.
Slightly on the shorter side angling into leg. Conway uses the depth of the crease and works it towards short fine leg. A maiden over from Jack Leach!
On a length, on off. Young blocks it off the back foot.
On the shorter side, on off. Young defends it off the back foot.
On a length, around off. Young rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Angling into middle, it is that length delivery again and Young defends it calmly towards the leg side.
Drifting on the pads. Young works it behind square on the leg side. Young looks for a single but is sent back.
Goes wider of the crease and angles a length delivery on middle. Young blocks it out.
Tossed up on off. Conway works it towards mid-wicket.
A flatter one on middle. Conway defends it towards the leg side.
Good from Leach! He bowls it around those footmarks, around off. It bounces sharply and tuns in a bit also, beats the outside edge of Conway's blade.
Fuller one on off. Conway drives it to long on for a single.
It is slightly short and bounces a bit extra. Young cuts but gets more of a thick outside edge. The ball travels towards the deep backward point region and he gets three runs.
A fuller one on middle. Conway works it to mid-wicket.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Young leaves it but there is a good inward movement after it passes the batter, it almost goes over the top of the off stump.
Full and straighter this time. Will Young defends it well.
Full and outside off stump. Will Young lets it go easily.
Straying in line this time, on the pads, slightly back of length. Will Young works it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Back of length again into the body of Devon Conway. He lets it go down the leg side and Ben Foakes makes another great diving save to his right and collects the ball.

Full and outside off. Devon Conway taps it towards cover and rushes for a quick single. Matthew Potts tumbles onto the ball and tries to throw it while falling, gets his radar wrong and concedes an extra run.
On the shorter side and turning away from around off. Young defends it towards the off side.
This is pushed quicker, outside off. Young with a good leave.
Flatter one again but bit shorter, around off. Young punches it to covers.
This time punches it towards sweeper cover as he gets back to another shortish delivery. A single taken.
Drifting on the pads. Conway works it to deep square leg for a single.
Darted on the pads. Young works it past square leg for a brace.
On a good length and outside off. Devon Conway taps it down to short leg.
On a good length again, slightly straighter. Devon Conway plays it back to the bowler.
Fuller this time, outside off stump. Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off. Devon Conway is not interested to play at it.
On a length, on off. Conway blocks it off the front foot.
Nicely bowled! A good-length delivery, around off. Conway looks to defend it but the ball shapes into him and beats the inside edge of his blade.
On the shorter side, around off. Young pushes it to point for a single.
Leach keeps it a bit short on off. Conway pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. It is quite fuller in length and Conway tries to drive it through covers. However, he ends up getting the inside edge onto his pads.
Turning into middle and Conway just turns it towards mid-wicket with the turn.
Angling on leg this time. Conway takes a single as he tucks it towards square leg.
Nicely tossed up on off. Young with a good stride forward and defends it.
Back of a length outside off stump. Devon Conway gets on top of it and plays it square of gully.
On a good length outside off stump. Defended towards the cover fielder.
Slightly fuller on off stump. Devon Conway fends it towards short mid off.
On a length outside off stump. Devon Conway plays it towards point.
Straighter line on a good length. Devon Conway works it towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller length on off stump. Devon Conway works it awkwardly towards square leg for a single. The ball seemed to stay slightly low.
A fuller delivery on middle. Conway works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker and slightly on the shorter side, around off. Young blocks it off the back foot.
Goes a bit fuller on off. Young with a front foot defence.
Nicely bowled! An arm ball that comes through with the angle on middle. Young goes back and defends it onto the turf.
A fuller one on off. Young with a gentle push towards covers. A single more added to the score.
FOUR! Conway brings out a reverse-sweep and finds the boundary this time! A fuller one on middle. Conway gets into his position early and reverse-sweeps it hard through point for a boundary.

Back of a length outside off stump. James Anderson gets some extra bounce off the pitch. Will Young is beaten on the outside and the England players go up in appeal. The umpire is unmoved and the skipper, Ben Stokes also shows less interest and hence they don't opt for the review. The replays later suggest that no bat was involved a great decision by Stokes once again.
Wider line and on a good length. Will Young lets it go this time.
James Anderson is getting good shape on the ball. Pitching outside off on a good length. Will Young makes a good leave.

Huge appeal once again. This one is on a good length outside off stump. It nips back dangerously and it raps the pads as Will Young tries to leave it. Umpire does not seem interested as it looks like the ball would not be hitting the stumps.
A fuller delivery on middle. Young works it through mid-wicket this time and the batters run three.
Comes 'round the wicket angling into middle. Conway blocks it out.
A fuller delivery on middle Young defends it with soft hands towards the leg side.
It is outside off and turning away. Young leaves it.
On the shorter side, on middle. Young works it towards the leg side.
A flatter one and quicker, around off. Young punches it to covers.
This is pushed quicker again, on off. Young goes back and blocks it off the back foot.
Nicely tossed up on off. However, it is equally well played by Young who gets forward and blocks it.
On a good length outside off. Devon Conway fends it with a cross bat towards point.
Back of length and way outside off stump. Devon Conway lets it go to the keeper.
On a good length but straighter. Devon Conway works it towards backward square leg for a single.
Fuller outside off stump. Will Young tries to drive at it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Full delivery outside off stump. Will Young does not offer a shot.

Beautiful delivery to end the over! James Anderson bowls a beautiful outswinger just outside off stump on a good length. Will Young is beaten all ends up and James Anderson would be wondering how he did not manage to get any nick off the bat there!
A fuller delivery on off. Conway blocks it out.
On the shorter side, around off. Conway mistimes his cut shot to point for a single.
FOUR! Good use of the feet! Tossed up on middle. Young skips down the track and lifts it over mid on for a boundary.
Slower in the air again, on off. Young defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Again he uses his feet and hits this over the infield! On middle and Young reaches the pitch of the ball to chip it towards the cow corner. The ball goes off the bounce into the fence.
Slower in pace, outside off. Young defends it towards the off side.
James Anderson is bowling around the wicket. Back of a length, outside off. Conway lets it go.
On a good length outside off stump. Some extra bounce again and Devon Conway plays it well, down to the gully fielder.
Slightly fuller outside off stump. Devon Conway lets it go with a flourish of his bat.
Back of a length and straighter this time. Hits Devon Conway high on the pads and England's appeal is turned down by the umpire.
On a good length outside off stump. Left alone again by Devon Conway.
Slighly fuller on an off stump line. Devon Conway knocks it towards mid off.
Pitches it on middle and it turns away a bit. Young goes back and works it towards square leg for a single.
Lovely tossed up, outside off. Conway defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Another reverse-sweep and Conway gets a boundary again! On off and Conway gets low to reverse-sweep it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in two now! On the shorter side, on middle. Conway goes back and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Very nicely played, uses the depth of the crease to a great effect.
FOUR! Make it three in a row! Shortish length outside off stump. Devon Conway gets on his back foot and punches it through covers for a beautiful boundary!
Quicker delivery on off. Conway blocks it off the back foot.
NO BALL! Loose delivery to start from Ben Stokes. Short and asking to be hit. Will Young smashes it straight to mid-wicket. Ben Stokes oversteps and has an extra delivery to bowl.
Short again,outside off stump. Will Young gets on his toes and plays it to covers.
Bangs it short into the surface ouside off stump. Will Young does not offer a shot.

FOUR! Ben Stokes finally alters his length. Goes fuller and straighter and induces an inside edge of Will Young as he tries to drive. The ball narrowly misses the stump and goes towards fine leg for a boundary!
Back of a length on the stumps. Keeps slightly low and Will Young just manages to keep it out.
A fuller delivery but way down the leg side. Young lets it go.
On a length angling into pads. Young works it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up on off. Young blocks it off the front foot.
Slower in the air, on off. Young pushes it back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off. Young punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Slower in the air, around off. Conway defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Another reverse-sweep and another boundary for Conway! Tossed up on middle. Conway reverse-sweeps it through the point region for a boundary.
Angling into leg. Conway works it to short fine leg.
Back of a length outside off stump. Will Young lets it go as the ball reaches the keeper.
On a good length just outside off. Nips back into Will Young, who defends it to covers.
Fuller this time on off stump. Will Young hurriedly puts his bat down and defends it towards mid-wicket.
Plenty of movement for Ben Stokes. Pitches on a good length and nips back into Will Young. Hits the pad and England players appeal half-heartedly.
Back of a length on off stump. Will Young judges it well and leaves as the ball goes over the stumps.
Ben Stokes is getting a nice bounce off the wicket here. Back of a length on off stump and Will Young rises with the bounce and nudges it towards square leg.
A flatter one on off. Conway defends it off the front foot.
This is full and around off. Conway sweeps but finds the fielder at short fine leg.

FOUR! Fifty for Devon Conway! He has missed out on scoring big runs so far in this series but with the kind of player he is, a big score is never too far away. A tossed up delivery on off. Conway reverse-sweeps it through backward point for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ohh...a wicket against the run of play this, Conway was looking so good out there in the middle. However, he has to walk back now and Leach provides a crucial breakthrough. This is fuller on middle. Conway goes for a sweep shot this time after a reverse-sweep in the previous delivery. He, however, gets a top edge and the ball goes in the air towards deep square leg. Jonny Bairstow there moves forward and takes a fine low catch diving forward.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Jack Leach

Commentary: On off and turning in. Henry Nicholls blocks it off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Jack Leach pitches it on middle and gets a good turn and bounce there. Henry Nicholls looks to reverse-sweep it but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards leg slip where Ben Stokes takes the catch. They appeal but the umpire says no. Stokes decides to take a review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved nor there is any glove and the Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing stumps. The original decision stays.
Back of a length, on off. Young pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Henry Nicholls blocks it out.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Stokes goes full angling into leg. Henry Nicholls looks to flick it but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is a stifled appeal but nothing serious. It is going down leg.

Ohh...almost drags it on! Back of a length, around off. Henry Nicholls blocks it onto the turf but the ball seems to be rolling back to the stumps. However, Henry Nicholls pushes the ball away with his boot just in time.
A fuller delivery on middle. Henry Nicholls flicks it to left of mid on.
On the shorter side, outside off. Young punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Slower in the air and fuller, outside off. Henry Nicholls defends it with soft hand towards the off side for a single.

FOUR! Young goes for the sweep shot and gets a bit of top edge but it falls in the vacant fine leg region and goes away towards the boundary. This one was pitched on middle and it is a bit of risky shot.
Darted around leg. Young looks to paddle it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal. The umpire though is unmoved. It is probably going down leg.
Tossed up and outside off. Young leaves it.
Shortish length, on off. Young goes back and blocks it out.
Slightly back of a length outside off stump. Angle into Henry Nicholls who defends it back.
Slightly short on off stump. Henry Nicholls leans back and pulls it to deep square leg for a brace.
Full delivery on off stump. Henry Nicholls defends firmly towards mid on.
NO BALL! Ben Stokes oversteps once again. Outside off stump and full. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Back of a length on off stump. Steps back and fends it towards cover.
Slightly fuller and outside off stump. Ben Stokes is constantly varying his length. Induces an inside edge onto pad once again.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Henry Nicholls carefully lets it go. That will be Tea on Day 4!
A fullish delivery, outside off to start. Young leaves it alone.
Full and on off stump. Defended back to the bowler.

FIFTY! And that's a half-century for Will Young! He has played really well to make sure New Zealand dont have to worry much. Full and outside off stump. Will Young knocks it to covers and takes a quick single.
Outside off, left alone.
A full delivery on middle. Henry Nicholls flicks it to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Henry Nicholls perishes early and the floodgates are truly opened up now for England to capitalize on. Henry Nicholls provides the easiest of catches to backward point. It is a short and wide delievery outside off, Henry Nicholls could have seen it sail past him but fell into the trap. He goes for an expensive shot and finds Alex Lees who takes a sharp catch. Trent Bridge errupts.
Howout: c Alex Lees b Matthew Potts

Commentary: Lovely delivery, bit of indecision from Young! A good-length delivery, outside off. Young first tries to push his bat towards the ball but pulls out at the last moment.
On a length, on off. Young blocks it out.
Lands it on a channel around off. Young makes a careful leave.
On a length, on off. Young blocks it from his crease.
Goes fuller on middle. Young gets his bat down in time. This is good bowling by Stokes, he is keeping the batter guessing all the time.
On a length, on middle. Young works it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Length ball outside off stump. Defended solidly by Will Young
Full and straight angling down leg side. Will Young tries to work it on the leg side but hits his pad and gets a single towards square leg.
Full and outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell moves accross and knocks it towards mid on,
A fuller delivery on the pads. Daryl Mitchell flicks it to fine leg for a single. He is off the mark!
FOUR! Short and punished by Young! Potts goes short and provides the width outside off. Young cuts it through point for a boundary.
Good comeback delivery. Angled into Will Young on a good length. The ball shapes away after pitching and beats Will Young's outside edge.
Full length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell comes forward only to tap it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Incredible shot! Daryl Mitchell gets his first boundary now. It is full and on off. Daryl Mitchell leans forward and creams it past mid off for a fine boundary.
Good length, angled into the pads. Daryl Mitchell comes inside the line and glances it down to fine leg for a brace.
Length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out solidly.
Very full, wide of off. Daryl Mitchell fends it to covers off the toe end of the his blade.
Angles it in, fuller and on middle. Daryl Mitchell stays back and nudges it to short mid-wicket.
Short and really wide. Will Young just turns his back to it and lets it go.
On a good length and closer to the stumps this time. Will Young feels for it and beats him.
Slightly fuller and angling into the pads. Will Young rotates the strike courtesy a leg bye towards square leg. England players appeal but clearly going down leg stump.
On a good length on off stump. Played towards mid-wicket.
Fuller this time on off stump. Knocked towards mid off.

Short delivery in line with the stumps. Daryl Mitchell ducks under it and the ball swings massively after passing the batter. Ben Foakes dives right towards the ball which keeps moving away from him and gives New Zealand 2 extra runs as byes.
Stokes goes full, drifting down leg. Will Young tries to glance it away but misses. Ben Foakes dives to his left and makes a great stop.

OUT! RUN OUT! A mix up in the middle and New Zealand are in a spot of bother now as they lose Will Young now. It is a length ball, on midde. Young tucks it to mid-wicket. Daryl Mitchell wants a single and he is out of his crease. Will Young is a tad late into his charge, which allows Ollie Pope to set himself up and throw it to Ben Stokes at the non-striker's end, who collects the ball and is quick to take the bails off. Even a desperate dive could not save Young here.
Howout: run out (Ollie Pope / Ben Stokes)

Commentary: Good length, outside off, jags back in a long way. Daryl Mitchell shoulders his arms and sees the ball go over the stumps.
This one angles in, on a length outside off, but leaves the batter after hitting the deck. Daryl Mitchell tries to chase it but fails to get any connection.
Full and on off. Daryl Mitchell tucks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone. Good carry for Stokes there!
Full and outside off stump. Tom Blundell watches keenly and raises his arms as he lets it go.
Straighter line on a good length. Tom Blundell comes across the stumps and tries to feel for it. Beats the outside edge and goes through to the keeper.
Fuller and straying down the leg side. Tom Blundell gets bat on it and works it to backward square leg for a single.
On a good length outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell shuffles across and plays it to mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery outside off stump. Defended towards covers.
Slighly fuller outside off stump. Tom Blundell plays at it and gets it through the gully region for a one run.
Good length and in the channel, with some extra bounce off the deck. Tom Blundell shoulders his arms without any hesitation.
FOUR! Nicely played! Tom Blundell gets his first boundary. It is full and outside off. Tom Blundell leans in and drives it through the gap at covers for a boundary.

Ben Foakes has been excellent behind the stumps. This is touch shorter, drifting down leg. Tom Blundell gets inside the line but is unable to tickle it away. Foakes dives to his left and gathers the ball nicely.
Around the hips, Blundell tucks it to square leg for a single.
Good length, on off, Mitchell works it to the on side.
NO BALL! A length ball, around off. Daryl Mitchell defends it out watchfully. Although, Stokes has to reload his final delivery as he oversteps this time.
Length and outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a good length outside off stump. Tom Blundell steps across, raises his arms, and lets the ball go.

Yorker just outside off stump. Tom Blundell tries to dig it out and misses the line of the ball. England players appeal but there is nothing really to it. There was a sound no doubt, but it was of the bat thumping the ground.
Full and outside off. Defended back to the bowler.
Full and outside off stump. Tom Blundell drives firmly to mid off.
Full and on the stumps. Tom Blundell gets across and plays it to mid-wicket for an easy single.
Full once again and directed at the pads. Daryl Mitchell steps across and flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, angled down leg. Daryl Mitchell flicks it off his pads through square leg for a brace.
Full length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell drives it to mid off on the front foot.
Two dots in a row! Full length, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it to the off side.
NO BALL! It is full and outside off. Daryl Mitchell looks to work it to the off side but gets it to mid-wicket off the inner half. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Good length, around middle, angled in. Daryl Mitchell stays back and defends it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell hits it in the ground. It goes over Stokes, but Stuart Broad comes in with a great effort at mid on to stop the ball.
On a length, outside off, left alone by Daryl Mitchell.
Floated full on the pads. Tom Blundell taps it down towards short leg.
Slightly short on middle stump. Tom Blundell steps back and punches it down to long on for a single.
Full and on middle. Daryl Mitchell drives it towards long on for one run.
Full on leg stump. Defendly solidly towards the short leg fielder.
Fuller on middle stump. Tom Blundell nudges it towards leg gully.
Full on off stump. Tom Blundell tries to work it towards mid-wicket but instead gets a leading edge through covers for a single.
Length ball, angling in. Tom Blundell tucks it through square leg for a single.
Length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Another one way outside off. Daryl Mitchell shoulders his arms at it.
Good-length delivery this time, that nips back in a touch. Daryl Mitchell uses the depth of the crease and blocks it out.
WIDE! A sharp bouncer now, on off. Daryl Mitchell ducks under it and the umpire signals a wide on height.
Length ball, on top of off. Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and defends it to mid on.
NO BALL! It is full and outside off. Daryl Mitchell pushes it to cover. Ben Stokes oversteps again and he has to reload his delivery. His 11th no ball of the match.
Length and on off. Daryl Mitchell flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full on off stump. Driven delicately towards long on for a single.
Full on middle stump. Tom Blundell steps forward and plays with a straight bat.
Full again on middle stump. Tom Blundell defends it down into the pitch.
Full delivery again but outside off stump. Tom Blundell defends it towards the bowler.
FOUR! CRACKED! It is short and outside off. Tom Blundell stays back and cuts it through covers for a boundary. The lead moves to 170.
Full and on off. Blundell defends it on his front foot.
Full length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell comes down the track and defends it into covers.
Full length, outside off. This is stayed down a little bit. Daryl Mitchell gets it down to third man and collects a brace.
What a ripper! A length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Daryl Mitchell tries to defend it out but does so inside the line the line to get beaten on the outside edge.
Length, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Good length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell walks yet again but decides to shoulders his arms, although he is tad late into his decision. The ball hits the blade and goes to the off side.
A length ball, slanting in. Daryl Mitchell tucks it off his hips and gets a single to square leg.
Full and wide. Turns away from Daryl Mitchell as he lets it go.
Slightly short outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell steps back and plays the turning ball towards covers.
Full and on off stump. Defended solidly to the short cover region.
Full and on middle. Daryl Mitchell drives it to long on for a single.
Flatter delivery outside off stump. Tom Blundell steps back and knocks it down towards covers.
Full agin outside of stump. Pushed towards silly point.
On a length, on off. Daryl Mitchell works it wide of mid on for a single.
Back of a length, on off at 128 kph. Tom Blundell blocks it solidly from his crease.
Continues with almost a same length and line and Tom Blundell is solid in his defence again.
Goes a bit fuller on off. Tom Blundell this time defends it off the front foot.
Broad decides to go a bit wider, outside off. It is on a length again and Tom Blundell lets it go.
He is back with his off stump line. Tom Blundell is solid in defence again.
A flatter one on middle. Daryl Mitchell punches it to long on for a single.

NOT OUT! Good review taken by Tom Blundell and the decision is overturned! A tossed up delivery, around off. Tom Blundell looks to defend it off the front foot. However, he misses as the ball turns away a bit. There is an appeal for a caught behind as there is some noise there and the umpire raises his finger. Tom Blundell reviews it straightaway and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Tom Blundell will continue.
A flatter one on off. Tom Blundell blocks it out.
Slower in the air, around off. Tom Blundell defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Good shot! This is darted on middle. Tom Blundell flicks it through mid-wicket and finds the gap, it races away towards the fence for a boundary.
Slower in the air, on off. Tom Blundell pushes it to covers. Good over by Leach, he is varying his pace nicely here.
On a length, on off. Daryl Mitchell defends it off the outside half of his blade towards point.
Comes wide of the crease and angles it fuller on middle. Daryl Mitchell defends it towards mid on.

Ohh... Ben Foakes has been so good throughout this Test match but this time he fails to connect this regulation delivery and batters runs two byes. Lands on a length, around off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone. Ben Foakes fails to collect it as it hits his thumb and two byes added to the total.
On a length, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Angling into middle and leg again. Daryl Mitchell works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Broad spills it down the leg side. It is on the shorter side as well and Tom Blundell lets it go.
Shorter and outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it off the front foot.
Pulls his length back a bit, around off. Daryl Mitchell with a defensive shot right under his eyes.
A flatter delivery and bit quicker. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
On the shorter side and turning away a bit. Daryl Mitchell pushes it to covers, without much timing though.
Pushed quicker and outside off. Bit fuller and Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery, around off. It comes back into Tom Blundell who decides to leave it. Good leave in the end!
On a length, on middle. Tom Blundell works it towards mid-wicket.
Goes fuller and angles it on off. Tom Blundell drives it off the inside half of his blade towards right of the bowler.
Drifting on the pads this time. Tom Blundell looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls towards square leg. A leg bye taken.
Serves a length delivery on off at 134 kph. Daryl Mitchell is happy to block it.
A good length delivery, around off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone. New Zealand are not taking any risks as of now, just happy to play the ball on its merit.
Tossed up nicely on off. Tom Blundell with a forward block.
Floated up in the air, on off. Tom Blundell skips down the track and drives it towards the cover fielder.
A flatter one on off. Tom Blundell blocks it.
The pace is slower this time, around off. Tom Blundell drives again but finds the cover fielder again.
Leach continues with the same line and length. Delivers it at 87 kph and Tom Blundell blocks it off the front foot.
This is a bit wider outside off. Tom Blundell pushes it gently towards the off side.
Broad goes short, around off. Daryl Mitchell resist playing the shot and lets it go.
Broad continues with the short-pitch stuff and delivers it down the leg side. Daryl Mitchell tries to pull it this time but misses.
A bouncer again and angling into the body. Daryl Mitchell looks to pull again but misses again and this time he gets hit on his elbow. That will hurt!
Good bouncer again but equally well played by Daryl Mitchell! A short ball on off. Daryl Mitchell rides the bounce and defends it with soft hand towards the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Daryl Mitchell works it towards the leg side.
Broad changes the angle for the last delivery but not his length, bangs it short on middle. Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.
Tossed up, on off. Tom Blundell skips down the track and drives it along the ground towards mid off.
Slightly shorter and around off. Tom Blundell blocks it off the back foot.
Short and wide, outside off. Tom Blundell goes back and tries to cut it. He gets the cue ends of his blade and the ball goes behind square on the off side for a single.
Slower in the air and outside off. Daryl Mitchell lets it go.
Short and wide outside off. Daryl Mitchell cuts it without much timing towards point.
Nicely flighted delivery on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Back of a length delivery outside off stump and Tom Blundell goes back and rises up to punch it past point. The fielder gives chase but the ball wins the race!

OUT! CAUGHT! England have broken this dreaded partnership! Short ball angled towards the shoulder of Tom Blundell. He could have let that one be but instead chooses to pull it. Does not get a good connection and ball goes aerially towards backward square leg where Ben Stokes takes a fine catch. He immediately points his finger towards the dressing room after taking that catch and the England coach Brendon McCullum gives a thumbs up to his skipper. Big wicket for England, Broad provides a crucial breakthrough!
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Leg stump line on a good length. Michael Bracewell nudges it to fine leg for a single.
Short again and going down leg side. Daryl Mitchell has failed to learn from the last wicket and tries to pull it. Misses the gloves by a whisker as it goes through to the keeper.
Slightly fuller and on the pads. Daryl Mitchell works it with the help of his pads to backward square leg and gets to the other side.
Around the wicket to the left-hander. Back of length outside off stump. Michael Bracewell steps back and defends it solidly.
Full, and on leg. Daryl Mitchell blocks it to the leg side.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell eases it to long on for a single.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Michael Bracewell blocks it on his front foot.

FOUR! A half-chance for Jack Leach although a tough one. It is full and outside off. Michael Bracewell comes down the track and smacks it down the ground. He hits it so hard that Jack Leach does not get much time to put his hand out as well.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Michael Bracewell and he has started well here. It is full and on off. Michael Bracewell gets low and slogs it to wide long on for a boundary.
Full, on off. Michael Bracewell tucks it to the leg side.
Back of a length on middle stump. Daryl Mitchell pulls it straight to square leg.
Short again slightly outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell steps across and tries to pull again but mistimes it to mid-wicket.
Around the wicket now to target the body. Short ball on leg stump. Daryl Mitchell continues to pull. A misfield at backward square leg allows Daryl Mitchell to get a single.

SIX! Michael Bracewell is looking dangerous! Short delivery again angled into Michael Bracewell who has no trouble timing his pull shot as he launches the ball over the deep square boundary for a massive six!
Stuart Broad goes over the wicket again and bowls a length ball down leg side. Left alone by Michael Bracewell.
Slower delivery this time, full and on the stumps. Michael Bracewell flicks it towards backward square leg for a single.
Floated and full, outside off. Bracewell blocks it on his front foot.
Flatter, on off. Michael Bracewell stays back and defends it out.
Around off, Bracewell tucks it to the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Bracewell works it to mid on for a single.
Full and on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it to the on side off the inner half.
Looped up, around off. Mitchell remains solid in his defense. A tidy over by Leach comes to an end.

FOUR! Giving it the charge! This debutant is here to make his mark! Matthew Potts comes around the wicket and bangs it in short outside off stump. Michael Bracewell has taken a few steps forward and cross-batted this above mid off for a one-bounce boundary!

FOUR! That's back-to-back boundaries! Back of a length delivery angled into the body. Michael Bracewell stays in the crease and pulls it through the square leg region between the two out-field players for a crunching boundary!
Better length this time and outside off stump. Michael Bracewell defends it towards cover.

OUT! CAUGHT! Michael Bracewell's entertaining cameo has come to an end! He has however brought New Zealand to a position of considerable safety! Not all that full in line with the stumps, Michael Bracewell gets in no position to drive the ball straight. He lofts it and finds Stuart Broad at mid on who takes a comfortable catch. England rejoice out of relief to see the back of Michael Bracewell as he walks out to a standing ovation.
Howout: c Stuart Broad b Matthew Potts

Commentary: BYE! A sharp bouncer, outside off. This one flies off the deck. Ben Foakes leaps but it is well over him. The batters collect a bye.
Length ball, on the pads. Daryl Mitchell flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Nicely played! Good length, angled down leg side. Daryl Mitchell gets inside the line and tickles it fine for a boundary.
Good length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell shoulders his arms at it.
Two dots in a row! On a length, wide outside off. Daryl Mitchell lets it be.
A length ball, on fourth stump. Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line and works it towards backward point off the outer half. The batters collect a brace.

OUT! RUN OUT! Tim Southee gets run out for a duck. Another one bites the dust for New Zealand. This does not look good at all. Poor communication by Daryl Mitchell. A length ball, around off. Daryl Mitchell guides it through backward point and runs hard for the first runs. He calls for the second, but as soon as he sees the ball decides against it, although it was a bit too late for Southee to get back. Zak Crawley throws it at the keeper and Ben Foakes completes the business.
Howout: run out (Zak Crawley / Ben Foakes)

Commentary: A short ball, on the bodyline. Matt Henry ducks under it.
On a good length outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell defends it to the offside as the bowler runs and collects it.
Slightly fuller and outside off stump. Matthew Potts attempts a slower ball but has no direction and Daryl Mitchell watches it go by to the keeper.
Straighter delivery angled into the pads off a good length. Daryl Mitchell looks to flick it but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls towards square leg. A leg bye taken.
WIDE! Matthew Potts has tried to angle it away from Daryl Mitchell from around the wicket. Gets his line completely wrong and 1st slip has to stop it. Wide called by the umpire.
Bouncer bowled outside leg stump. Matt Henry easily ducks under this one.

FOUR! Well hit by Matt Henry! Full length delivery outside off stump. Matt Henry steps forward and drills it through cover for a boundary. Matthew Potts attempting a yorker and providing a half-volley instead.
Bangs it in hard off the wicket, and tucks Matt Henry in who plays it well off his pads towards backward square leg.
Good length, outside off, shaping away a touch. Daryl Mitchell tries to defend it out but misses.
Length ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell pushes it to point for one,.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Henry ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Henry hops and somehow manages to sway away from the line of the delivery.
FOUR! A low full toss, on off. Henry slams it down the ground for a boundary.
Back of a length, on middle. Henry ducks under it watchfully.
Short ball way over Daryl Mitchell's head. He does not even have to duck to let that one go.
Short again angled into the body. Daryl Mitchell ducks under the ball this time.
On a good length outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell defends it confidently towards cover.
Short ball in line with the stumps bowled again and Daryl Mitchell casually ducks under it and lets it go.
Back of a length outside off stump. Walks across and fends it off easily towards point.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell stays back and defends it to the leg side. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4.
Flighted delivery, full and on off, Henry presents a defensive bat and pushes it to covers.

PUT DOWN! Plenty of catches have gone down in this Test match. Quicker through the air, around off, Henry tries to defend it with firm hands but edges it behind. Root goes down to his right at first slip but fails to grab it.
Flatter on off, blocked from the back foot.
Leans forward to a full ball and push-drives it to covers.
Goes on the back foot to a short ball and punches it through the line. Finds backward point.
Shortish and close to off, Henry cuts it from the back foot to point. The fielder fumbles slightly but no run is taken.
On a good length, angling towards the leg side. Daryl Mitchell fails to work it around and it goes off his pads to the leg side. They collect a leg bye.
Back of a length, targeting Matt Henry's body. He does well to lean back and get under it.
Still slightly short and outside the off stump. Matt Henry lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Matt Henry showing he can bat! Back of a length outside the off stump. Matt Henry gets on his back foot and punches it beautifully past point for a boundary.
Ben Stokes goes slightly fuller this time, in line with the stumps, Matt Henry plays it straight back to the bowler.
NO BALL! Ben Stokes continues bowling no balls. He is called back again to bowl the delivery once again. Bouncer bowled outside the off stump. Matt Henry tries to upper-cut it but misses the ball.
Back of a length outside off, Matt Henry sways out of the way and lets it go through to the keeper.
Floated delivery, full and around middle, Mitchell gets down and paddles it down to fine leg. Broad does well near the fence to stop a certain boundary. The veteran saves two for his team.
Bowls it quicker through the air, flat and short on middle, Daryl moves back and nudges it in front of square leg for one.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Henry drives it off the inner half, down to long on, for a run.
Fullish again, around off, Mitchell drives it back and Leach stops it with a dive to his left.
Floated delivery, full and around off, Mitchell presses forward and defends it with the spin to covers.
Quicker and around leg, Daryl works it off his pads but finds mid-wicket. Matt Henry will be on strike for the start of the next over.
Floors the batter! Beautiful bouncer nipping back into Matt Henry. He sways back to avoid the ball and falls back on the floor.
Short again, in line with the stumps. Henry ducks well this time.
Ben Stokes is bowling with some fire here! Short ball again and directed well into Matt Henry, He sways back and falls on his back again.
Goes fuller this time on the stumps. Matt Henry works it off his pads to square leg.
Goes back to bowling short! Matt Henry does not look very comfortable dealing with these short balls as he sways back again.
Ben Stokes goes round the wicket with a leg slip in place. Short and outside leg stump. Matt Henry lets this one go easily.
Loopy and full, around off, it's defended back safely.
Quicker and on off, blocked from the crease to the off side.
Arm ball, landing around middle and skidding down the leg side, Daryl moves back and eases it to deep square leg for a run.
Fuller delivery, on middle, Henry is on the front foot and defends it to short cover.
Leach serves it full again, around off, Matt drives but finds the cover fielder again.
Tossed up, around off, defended watchfully to the off side.
Fuller delivery outside the off stump. Daryl Mitchell works it through backward point for a single. The lead touches 250!
Shortish and angling into the body. Matt Henry keeps his eye on the ball and sways back.
Short again and straighter this time. Matt Henry chooses to sway back instead of ducking and looks awkward getting out of the way.

FOUR! Gets a hold of that one! Back of a length outside off, the ball doesn't rise up much and Matt Henry gets on his toes and smashes it through cover-point where a misfield allows him to get a boundary! It landed on one of the practice pitches and Broad was the unlucky one to experience the bad bounce.
Straighter on a good length! Matt Henry knocks it off his waist towards square leg.
Straight again on a good length. Matt Henry plays it with a straight bat back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery, full and on off, Mitchell is on the front foot as he defends.
Serves it slightly quicker and fuller, around off, it's defended again, this time to the left of covers.
Bowls it full but the line changes towards middle and angle, Mitchell goes down and sweeps it to fine leg for two. The keeper had moved in anticipation but still failed to stop it.
Eases a fuller delivery down to long on and rotates the strike.
Fullish and on off, defended easily by Henry.
Leach drops it full and on off, Matt Henry draws forward in defense. Four overs left for the second new ball.
On a good length outside off, Daryl Mitchell steps across the stumps and defends it towards gully.
Full delivery outside off. Daryl Mitchell puts his front foot forward and nicely drives it to deep cover. All fielders on the off side are at the boundary to allow an easy single.
Ben Stokes continues bowling short to Matt Henry! Back of a length in line with the stumps. Matt Henry has mastered the art of swaying away.
Slightly back of a length on off, Matt Henry rises up and plays at the ball which gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Around the wicket, back of a length into Matt Henry. He skips up and works it to square leg.

Ben Stokes finally gets Matt Henry to play at a short ball. This rises into Matt Henry and instead of getting out of the way, he puts his glove to it. Fortunately for him, the ball flies over gully and lands safely! Matt Henry gets lucky and Ben Stokes is really bending his back here without any luck.
Broad begins from 'round the wicket and angles across a shortish ball outside off, Henry leans back a bit and lets it be.
Short again, outside off and leaving the batter with the angle, Henry offers no shot.
Fractionally short again, outside off, Henry stays on the back foot and plays it down defensively to point.
Broad bends his back to go short, this time close to the off stump, Henry sways away.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The resilience of Matt Henry is over. Stuart Broad digs it in short again, around middle and off. Henry spots that there is no fielder in the deep on the leg side and decides to take on the short delivery. Attempts to pull but only manages to edge it to Ben Foakes. England have got the breakthrough they were looking for and it has come with the second new ball not too far away. Lead for the Kiwis is 259.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Broad greets the new batter with a short ball on middle and off, Kyle walks across the stumps and defends it on the leg side. A bit uppish but it's away from short leg. A wicket maiden for Broad.
Full toss outside off as Ben Stokes attempts a slower delivery. Daryl Mitchell knocks it to covers for a single.
Kyle Jamieson is not ducking for these short balls! Short and in line with the stumps. Kyle Jamieson pulls it uppishly towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length outside off. Daryl Mitchell steps across and pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Short and angling down the leg side. Kyle Jamieson does an awkward ducking action but the ball is away from him.
Short ball on off stump. Kyle Jamieson tries to pull at this but it is too high and he misses it altogether.
Stokes digs it in short, Jamieson ducks.
Lands it on a good length and outside off, Mitchell has so far restrained himself from going hard with his shots. He calmly plays it down softly to backward point and picks up a run.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Broad has another wicket and he has bounced out the tall man. It's short and well-directed at the batter, at 83 mph, Jamieson hangs across on the back foot and attempts to pull. He fails to connect properly though and gets a top edge behind to the keeper. Foakes grabs a brilliant catch despite getting a bit wrong-footed and New Zealand lose their ninth wicket.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Bouncer down the leg side, Boult allows it through to the keeper.
Short again, around leg, Boult steps back and tries to pull but misses. Is it called a no ball? No clarity although the on-air commentators are talking about it. Nothing from the umpire.
Broad continues to bang it in short, around leg, Boult is expecting it and ducks easily.
Another bumper is ducked safely by Boult to complete the over. Over to Daryl Mitchell now.
Slower delivery, full and outside off stump. Daryl Mitchell defends it firmly towards covers
On a good length outside off. Ben Stokes slows down his pace and Daryl Mitchell raises his arms and lets it go.
On a good length on middle and leg stump. Daryl Mitchell works it to deep square leg and turns down the single. The crowd disapproves and believes in Trent Boult's batting abilities.
Straight delivery on a good length. Daryl Mitchell knocks it towards long off and takes a single this time.
Short delivery down leg side. Trent Boult moves towards the off stump and lets it go through to the keeper.

Length ball on middle. Trent Boult works it wide of mid on and immediately calls for two. Trent Boult now owns the record for the most runs at number 11 in Test cricket (625). Tim Southee comes out of the dressing room and claps for his bowling partner.
Short and wide outside off, Mitchell cuts it to deep point and denies the run.

FOUR! Bang! Daryl Mitchell loves his pull shot. Gets one short ball in his trajectory and nails it to the deep mid-wicket fence. The fielder in the deep, Ben Stokes, lost the ball, and had no idea where it went.

FOUR! Fifty for Daryl Mitchell, not through a convincing shot though. Short again from Broad, Daryl Mitchell drags his attempted pull shot, off the inside edge, and it scoots down to fine leg for a boundary. What a Test series this is turning out to be for Daryl!
Short and outside off, Mitchell mistimes his flat-batted shot back towards the bowler.
Slower and on a length around off, DM defends it back towards the bowler again.
Very full and on off, Daryl Mitchell drills it down the ground but finds mid on. Boult will be on strike now.
Short and outside off. Trent Boult cross-bats it in the air beyond mid on for a brace.

FOUR! Trent Boult is playing some unorthodox shots here! Short and in line with the stump. Trent Boult takes a step back and opens his body to play a cross-batted shot once again down towards long off for a boundary!

FOUR! Trent Boult is adding some valuable runs to the New Zealand score! Ben Stokes persists with the short ball and angling into the batter. Trent Boult steps out towards the leg side and smashes this over cover-point for a wonderful boundary.
Short again into the body. Trent Boult moves out of the way and slashes at it but is beaten this time.
FOUR! Trent Boult is celebrating his batting record! Short ball angled in, Trent Boult pulls this and connects magnificently past the diving mid-wicket fielder for the third boundary in the over!
Ben Stokes gets more behind this short ball as it rises higher and goes through to the keeper. 14 from the over!
Delivers it on a good length, outside off, Mitchell watches the line and makes a leave. No movement there.
Angles in a length ball, around off, Mitchell pushes it away with an angled bat. The ball rolls through cover-point, the single is available but Mitchell denies it.
An attempted inswinger, sliding down the leg side, Daryl tries to flick but misses. It takes his thigh pad and runs down towards fine leg.
Fuller and on off, Mitchell walks forward and across before flicking it in the gap at deep mid-wicket for two.
Beauty! Broad serves it full and outside off, Mitchell walks forward again and tries to drive but it nips away a shade to beat the outside edge.
SIX! Smashed down the ground! Fuller in length, around off, Mitchell clears his front leg and launches it over long on for a biggie. Lead moves to 296.
Straight delivery, on a good length. Trent Boult gives himself room and tries to smash the ball. Misses it and the ball goes over the stumps by a whisker.
Straight and in line with the stumps. Trent Boult gets across the stumps and works it towards backward square leg for a single.
On a good length outside off. Daryl Mitchell plays it to backward point and gives Trent Boult the strike.

OUT! CAUGHT! The entertainment is over! Back of a length, around middle, Trent Boult steps back and throws his bat at it. It comes off the toe end and goes straight to Ben Stokes at mid off. The English skipper gleefully accepts the catch and New Zealand are all out for 284.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b James Anderson

Commentary: FOUR! This is a gorgeous way to get the chase running. Fuller in length and outside off, Alex Lees drills his drive through covers and finds the gap.
FOUR! Alex Lees is setting the perfect tone for this chase. Southee delivers it full again, outside off and there is no movement. Lees just hits it through the line and beats the cover-point fielder.
Southee switches to 'round the wicket and lands it on a length around off, Lees pushes it with an angled bat to point.

FOUR! Edgy! Southee serves it on a length and close to off, Alex Lees sticks back to defend it with an angled bat but it takes the outside edge and beats the gully fielder to his right. Three boundaries in the first over.
Full and outside off, on a driving length, Lees offers no shot.
Angles in a length ball on off, Alex Lees defends it from the back foot.
Full and outside off stump, angling away from Zak Crawley. He leaves it alone.
Slightly fuller this time outside off stump. Zak Crawley is not interested in getting the bat to it.
On a good length closer to the stumps this time. Angling away and beats Zak Crawley as he hangs his bat to it.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time Boult gets the edge! Wonderful bowling. He delivers it on a good length, just outside off stump and takes it away with the angle. Zak Crawley could have let it go but instead tries to play at it inside the line. Gets an outside edge that flies to Tim Southee at second slip. New Zealand strike early and the game is on!
Howout: c Tim Southee b Trent Boult

Commentary: Angling away from the batter, on a good length, Pope covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Beaten all ends up! Trent Boult takes a length ball away from the right-hander, with his natural angle, Pope pushes inside the line and misses. A wicket maiden!
In the channel outside off, Alex leaves it alone.
Another delivery outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Lees is playing with a lot of fluency. Short in length and wide outside off, Alex Lees rocks back and slaps it through backward point for a boundary. He is dealing in boundaries.
Serves it outside off, Alex offers no shot.
Another delivery in the channel outside off, Lees has nothing to do with it. He is picking his shots smartly.
On a length, around middle, Alex Lees uses the angle of the bowler and works it through square leg for a run.
Back of a length wide outside off. Alex Lees lets it go.
Straighter on a good length. Alex Lees works it uppishly square of mid-wicket for a couple.
FOUR! 5th boundary for Alex Lees! Trent Boult goes fuller outside off. Alex Lees drives it straight past mid off and the ball beats the fielder to the boundary.
Full and on the stumps. Alex Lees tries to flick it towards mid-wicket, but mistimes it and is disappointed with himself.
Full delivery on middle and leg. Shapes back in slightly and Alex Lees works it wide of mid on for a single.
Full length outside off and angling away. Ollie Pope leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Starts by angling away a length ball outside off, Lees allows it through.
Another delivery landing on a length and going quite wide outside off, Lees is not chasing it.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease towards mid off.
Fuller one, on the pads, Lees clips it towards square leg.
Taps a length ball down to cover-point and collects a single.
Full and angling in from around off, Pope goes forward and across as he flicks, but finds mid on.
Full and outside off stump. Left alone by Alex Lees.

FOUR! Alex Lees looks in sublime touch! Slightly back of a length and a little bit of width, Alex Lees goes on his back foot and punches it past point for a boundary! New Zealand need to see the back of Alex Lees as he is running away with the show!
Fuller outside off, Alex Lees fends it off as it gets the edge of the top part of the bat towards point.
Short delivery outside off. Alex Lees lets this one go.
Full and on middle stump. Alex Lees shows the face of his bat as he defends it towards mid on.
Fuller in length and on off. Alex Lees punches it to mid on.
Ooohhh... this one stays low. Henry dishes out a length ball, around off, Pope tries to defend but it goes past the bottom half of his blade.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
FOUR! Pope is away! Shortish and around off, Pope gets on top of the bounce and wristily pulls it through square leg for a boundary. Fine shot to open your account.
Angles in a length ball around off, Pope tries to work it around but misses. He is pinged on the front thigh pad. The bowler appeals for an lbw but to no avail.
Fuller and on off, Pope defends it back towards the bowler.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
On a good length on off stump. Defended back to the bowler by Alex Lees.
Fuller outside off stump. Alex Lees leans towards the ball and plays at it, gets an inside edge towards widish mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball outside off. Ollie Pope uses his wrists and works it on the leg side and tries for a single which is not there.
On a good length around off stump. Ollie Pope works it off his waist to fine leg for a single.
Full and on middle. Alex Lees knocks it towards mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off stump. Blocked towards the cover region.
Around off, on a length, Pope defends.
Fuller and around off, Pope works it off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Lands it on a length and around off, Pope offers a straight bat to defend but it takes the inner edge and rolls in front of square leg. They cross for a run.
Pitches it up and around off, Lees brings his bat down and pushes it away to mid off.
Fuller in length and on middle, Lees works it off his pads, good timing but the ball finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Delivers it on a good length, around off, Alex Lees defends it from the back foot to the off side. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 5!
